  66 ENABLE_COND_V2 = os.getenv("TF_ENABLE_COND_V2", "0") != "0"
  67 # Note: Setting this to True is not sufficient to switch to the v2 while_loop.
  68 # Users must also import the while_v2 module to set the _while_v2 module
  69 # variable above. We do this to avoid a circular dependency:
  70 # control_flow_ops -> while_v2 -> gradients_impl -> control_flow_ops
  71 # A ValueError is raised in tf.while_loop if this is set to True and the
  72 # `_while_v2` module is not set.
  73 ENABLE_WHILE_V2 = os.getenv("TF_ENABLE_WHILE_V2", "0") != "0"

  81 def _summarize_eager(tensor, summarize=None):
  82   """Returns a summarized string representation of eager `tensor`.
  83 
  84   Args:
  85     tensor: EagerTensor to summarize
  86     summarize: Include these many first elements of `array`
  87   """
  88   # reshape((-1,)) is the fastest way to get a flat array view
  89   if tensor._rank():  # pylint: disable=protected-access
  90     flat = tensor.numpy().reshape((-1,))
  91     lst = [str(x) for x in flat[:summarize]]
  92     if len(lst) < flat.size:
  93       lst.append("...")
  94   else:
  95     # tensor.numpy() returns a scalar for zero dimensional arrays
  96     if summarize != 0:
  97       lst = [str(tensor.numpy())]
  98     else:
  99       lst = []
 100 
 101   return ", ".join(lst)

 107 # Assert and Print are special symbols in python, so we must
 108 # use an upper-case version of them.
 109 @tf_export("debugging.Assert", "Assert")
 110 @tf_should_use.should_use_result
 111 def Assert(condition, data, summarize=None, name=None):
 112   """Asserts that the given condition is true.
 113 
 114   If `condition` evaluates to false, print the list of tensors in `data`.
 115   `summarize` determines how many entries of the tensors to print.
 116 
 117   NOTE: In graph mode, to ensure that Assert executes, one usually attaches
 118   a dependency:
 119 
 120   ```python
 121   # Ensure maximum element of x is smaller or equal to 1
 122   assert_op = tf.Assert(tf.less_equal(tf.reduce_max(x), 1.), [x])
 123   with tf.control_dependencies([assert_op]):
 124     ... code using x ...
 125   ```
 126 
 127   Args:
 128     condition: The condition to evaluate.
 129     data: The tensors to print out when condition is false.
 130     summarize: Print this many entries of each tensor.
 131     name: A name for this operation (optional).
 132 
 133   Returns:
 134     assert_op: An `Operation` that, when executed, raises a
 135     `tf.errors.InvalidArgumentError` if `condition` is not true.
 136     @compatibility{eager} returns None.
 137 
 138   Raises:
 139     @compatibility{eager} `tf.errors.InvalidArgumentError` if `condition`
 140     is not true
 141   """
 142   if context.executing_eagerly():
 143     if not condition:
 144       xs = ops.convert_n_to_tensor(data)
 145       data_str = [_summarize_eager(x, summarize) for x in xs]
 146       raise errors.InvalidArgumentError(
 147           node_def=None,
 148           op=None,
 149           message="Expected '%s' to be true. Summarized data: %s" %
 150           (condition, "\n".join(data_str)))
 151     return
 152 
 153   with ops.name_scope(name, "Assert", [condition, data]) as name:
 154     xs = ops.convert_n_to_tensor(data)
 155     if all([x.dtype in {dtypes.string, dtypes.int32} for x in xs]):
 156       # As a simple heuristic, we assume that string and int32 are
 157       # on host to avoid the need to use cond. If it is not case,
 158       # we will pay the price copying the tensor to host memory.
 159       return gen_logging_ops._assert(condition, data, summarize, name="Assert")
 160     else:
 161       condition = ops.convert_to_tensor(condition, name="Condition")
 162 
 163       def true_assert():
 164         return gen_logging_ops._assert(
 165             condition, data, summarize, name="Assert")
 166 
 167       guarded_assert = cond(condition, no_op, true_assert, name="AssertGuard")
 168       if context.executing_eagerly():
 169         return
 170       return guarded_assert.op

 173 def _Identity(data, name=None):
 174   """Return a tensor with the same shape and contents as the input tensor.
 175 
 176   Args:
 177     data: A Tensor.
 178     name: A name for this operation (optional).
 179 
 180   Returns:
 181     A Tensor with the same type and value as the input Tensor.
 182   """
 183   data = ops.internal_convert_to_tensor_or_indexed_slices(data, as_ref=True)
 184   if isinstance(data, ops.Tensor):
 185     if data.dtype._is_ref_dtype:  # pylint: disable=protected-access
 186       return gen_array_ops.ref_identity(data, name=name)
 187     else:
 188       return array_ops.identity(data, name=name)
 189   else:
 190     if not isinstance(data, (ops.IndexedSlices, sparse_tensor.SparseTensor)):
 191       raise TypeError("Type %s not supported" % type(data))
 192     values = _Identity(data.values, name=name)
 193     indices = array_ops.identity(data.indices, name="indices")
 194     if isinstance(data, ops.IndexedSlices):
 195       dense_shape = data.dense_shape
 196       if dense_shape is not None:
 197         dense_shape = array_ops.identity(dense_shape, name="dense_shape")
 198       return ops.IndexedSlices(values, indices, dense_shape)
 199     else:
 200       dense_shape = array_ops.identity(data.dense_shape, name="dense_shape")
 201       return sparse_tensor.SparseTensor(indices, values, dense_shape)

 204 def _NextIteration(data, name=None):
 205   data = ops.internal_convert_to_tensor_or_indexed_slices(data, as_ref=True)
 206   if isinstance(data, ops.Tensor):
 207     if data.dtype._is_ref_dtype:  # pylint: disable=protected-access
 208       return ref_next_iteration(data, name=name)
 209     else:
 210       return next_iteration(data, name=name)
 211   else:
 212     if not isinstance(data, (ops.IndexedSlices, sparse_tensor.SparseTensor)):
 213       raise TypeError("Type %s not supported" % type(data))
 214     values = _NextIteration(data.values, name=name)
 215     indices = next_iteration(data.indices, name="indices")
 216     if isinstance(data, ops.IndexedSlices):
 217       dense_shape = data.dense_shape
 218       if dense_shape is not None:
 219         dense_shape = next_iteration(dense_shape, name="dense_shape")
 220       return ops.IndexedSlices(values, indices, dense_shape)
 221     else:
 222       dense_shape = next_iteration(data.dense_shape, name="dense_shape")
 223       return sparse_tensor.SparseTensor(indices, values, dense_shape)

 226 def _Enter(data,
 227            frame_name,
 228            is_constant=False,
 229            parallel_iterations=10,
 230            use_ref=True,
 231            use_input_shape=True,
 232            name=None):
 233   """Creates or finds a child frame, and makes `data` available to it.
 234 
 235   The unique `frame_name` is used by the `Executor` to identify frames. If
 236   `is_constant` is true, `data` is a constant in the child frame; otherwise
 237   it may be changed in the child frame. At most `parallel_iterations`
 238   iterations are run in parallel in the child frame.
 239 
 240   Args:
 241     data: The tensor to be made available to the child frame.
 242     frame_name: The name of the child frame.
 243     is_constant: If true, the output is constant within the child frame.
 244     parallel_iterations: The number of iterations allowed to run in parallel.
 245     use_ref: If true, use ref_enter if data is of ref type.
 246     name: A name for this operation (optional).
 247 
 248   Returns:
 249     The same tensor as `data`.
 250   """
 251   data = ops.internal_convert_to_tensor_or_indexed_slices(data, as_ref=True)
 252   if isinstance(data, ops.Tensor):
 253     if data.dtype._is_ref_dtype and use_ref:  # pylint: disable=protected-access
 254       result = gen_control_flow_ops.ref_enter(
 255           data, frame_name, is_constant, parallel_iterations, name=name)
 256     else:
 257       result = gen_control_flow_ops.enter(
 258           data, frame_name, is_constant, parallel_iterations, name=name)
 259     if use_input_shape:
 260       result.set_shape(data.get_shape())
 261     return result
 262   else:
 263     if not isinstance(data, (ops.IndexedSlices, sparse_tensor.SparseTensor)):
 264       raise TypeError("Type %s not supported" % type(data))
 265     values = _Enter(
 266         data.values,
 267         frame_name,
 268         is_constant,
 269         parallel_iterations=parallel_iterations,
 270         use_input_shape=use_input_shape,
 271         name=name)
 272     indices = gen_control_flow_ops.enter(
 273         data.indices,
 274         frame_name,
 275         is_constant,
 276         parallel_iterations,
 277         name="indices")
 278     if use_input_shape:
 279       indices.set_shape(data.indices.get_shape())
 280     if isinstance(data, ops.IndexedSlices):
 281       dense_shape = data.dense_shape
 282       if dense_shape is not None:
 283         dense_shape = gen_control_flow_ops.enter(
 284             dense_shape,
 285             frame_name,
 286             is_constant,
 287             parallel_iterations,
 288             name="dense_shape")
 289         if use_input_shape:
 290           dense_shape.set_shape(data.dense_shape.get_shape())
 291       return ops.IndexedSlices(values, indices, dense_shape)
 292     else:
 293       dense_shape = gen_control_flow_ops.enter(
 294           data.dense_shape,
 295           frame_name,
 296           is_constant,
 297           parallel_iterations,
 298           name="dense_shape")
 299       if use_input_shape:
 300         dense_shape.set_shape(data.dense_shape.get_shape())
 301       return sparse_tensor.SparseTensor(indices, values, dense_shape)

 304 def exit(data, name=None):  # pylint: disable=redefined-builtin
 305   """Exits the current frame to its parent frame.
 306 
 307   Exit makes its input `data` available to the parent frame.
 308 
 309   Args:
 310     data: The tensor to be made available to the parent frame.
 311     name: A name for this operation (optional).
 312 
 313   Returns:
 314     The same tensor as `data`.
 315   """
 316   data = ops.internal_convert_to_tensor_or_indexed_slices(data, as_ref=True)
 317   if isinstance(data, ops.Tensor):
 318     if data.dtype._is_ref_dtype:  # pylint: disable=protected-access
 319       return gen_control_flow_ops.ref_exit(data, name)
 320     else:
 321       return gen_control_flow_ops._exit(data, name)
 322   else:
 323     if not isinstance(data, (ops.IndexedSlices, sparse_tensor.SparseTensor)):
 324       raise TypeError("Type %s not supported" % type(data))
 325     values = exit(data.values, name=name)
 326     indices = gen_control_flow_ops._exit(data.indices, name="indices")
 327     if isinstance(data, ops.IndexedSlices):
 328       dense_shape = data.dense_shape
 329       if dense_shape is not None:
 330         dense_shape = gen_control_flow_ops._exit(dense_shape, name)
 331       return ops.IndexedSlices(values, indices, dense_shape)
 332     else:
 333       dense_shape = gen_control_flow_ops._exit(data.dense_shape, name)
 334       return sparse_tensor.SparseTensor(indices, values, dense_shape)

 337 def switch(data, pred, dtype=None, name=None):
 338   """Forwards `data` to an output determined by `pred`.
 339 
 340   If `pred` is false, the `data` input is forwarded to the first output.
 341   Otherwise, the data goes to the second output.
 342 
 343   This op handles `Tensor`s and `IndexedSlices`.
 344 
 345   Args:
 346     data: The tensor to be forwarded to the appropriate output.
 347     pred: A scalar that specifies which output port will receive data.
 348     dtype: Optional element type for the returned tensor. If missing,
 349            the type is inferred from the type of `value`.
 350     name: A name for this operation (optional).
 351 
 352   Returns:
 353     `(output_false, output_true)`: If `pred` is true, data will be forwarded
 354     to `output_true`, otherwise it goes to `output_false`.
 355   """
 356   with ops.name_scope(name, "Switch", [data, pred]) as name:
 357     data = ops.internal_convert_to_tensor_or_indexed_slices(
 358         data, dtype=dtype, name="data", as_ref=True)
 359     pred = ops.convert_to_tensor(pred, name="pred")
 360     if isinstance(data, ops.Tensor):
 361       return gen_control_flow_ops.switch(data, pred, name=name)
 362     else:
 363       if not isinstance(data, (ops.IndexedSlices, sparse_tensor.SparseTensor)):
 364         raise TypeError("Type %s not supported" % type(data))
 365       val, ind = data.values, data.indices
 366       val_f, val_t = gen_control_flow_ops.switch(val, pred, name=name)
 367       ind_f, ind_t = gen_control_flow_ops.switch(ind, pred, name="indices")
 368       if isinstance(data, ops.IndexedSlices):
 369         dense_shape = data.dense_shape
 370         if dense_shape is not None:
 371           dense_shape_f, dense_shape_t = gen_control_flow_ops.switch(
 372               dense_shape, pred, name="dense_shape")
 373         else:
 374           dense_shape_f, dense_shape_t = None, None
 375         return (ops.IndexedSlices(val_f, ind_f, dense_shape_f),
 376                 ops.IndexedSlices(val_t, ind_t, dense_shape_t))
 377       else:
 378         dense_shape = data.dense_shape
 379         dense_shape_f, dense_shape_t = gen_control_flow_ops.switch(
 380             data.dense_shape, pred, name="dense_shape")
 381         return (sparse_tensor.SparseTensor(ind_f, val_f, dense_shape_f),
 382                 sparse_tensor.SparseTensor(ind_t, val_t, dense_shape_t))

 385 def _SwitchRefOrTensor(data, pred, name="Switch"):
 386   """Forwards `data` to an output determined by `pred`.
 387 
 388   If `pred` is false, the `data` input is forwarded to the first output.
 389   Otherwise, the data goes to the second output.
 390 
 391   This op handles `Tensor`s and `IndexedSlices`.
 392 
 393   Args:
 394     data: The tensor to be forwarded to the appropriate output.
 395     pred: A scalar that specifies which output port will receive data.
 396     name: A name for this operation (optional).
 397 
 398   Returns:
 399     `(output_false, output_true)`: If `pred` is true, data will be forwarded to
 400     `output_true`, otherwise it goes to `output_false`.
 401 
 402   Raises:
 403     TypeError: if data is not a Tensor or IndexedSlices
 404   """
 405   data = ops.convert_to_tensor_or_indexed_slices(data, name="data")
 406   # NOTE(vrv): ops.colocate_with(data, ignore_existing=True) below
 407   # addresses the following scenario.
 408   #
 409   # Assume you execute Optimizer.apply_gradients() in a branch of a cond().
 410   #
 411   # 1. The update op is created inside a `with ops.colocate(var):` block
 412   #
 413   # 2. Some tensor `data` is captured and a switch is created in a
 414   #    `with ops.colocate_with(data):` block.
 415   #
 416   # with ops.colocate_with(var):
 417   #  with ops.colocate_with(data):
 418   #    op = ...
 419   #
 420   # var and data may be pinned to different devices, so we want to ops
 421   # created within ops.colocate_with(data) to ignore the existing stack.
 422   with ops.colocate_with(data, ignore_existing=True):
 423     if isinstance(data, ops.Tensor):
 424       if data.dtype._is_ref_dtype:  # pylint: disable=protected-access
 425         return ref_switch(data, pred, name=name)
 426     return switch(data, pred, name=name)

 429 def merge(inputs, name=None):
 430   """Returns the value of an available element of `inputs`.
 431 
 432   This op tests each of the tensors in `inputs` in turn to determine if any of
 433   them is available. If it finds an available tensor, it returns it and its
 434   index in `inputs`.
 435 
 436   It is an error if more than one tensor in `inputs` is available. If no tensor
 437   in `inputs` is available, the returned tensor and index are not set.
 438 
 439   This op handles both `Tensor`s and `IndexedSlices`. If inputs has a mix of
 440   `Tensor`s and `IndexedSlices`, all inputs are converted to IndexedSlices
 441   before merging.
 442 
 443   Args:
 444     inputs: The input tensors, at most one of which is available.
 445     name: A name for this operation (optional).
 446 
 447   Returns:
 448     A tuple containing the chosen input tensor and its index in `inputs`.
 449 
 450   Raises:
 451     ValueError: If any of the inputs is None, or inputs are IndexedSlices and
 452       some but not all have a dense_shape property.
 453   """
 454   if any([inp is None for inp in inputs]):
 455     raise ValueError("At least one of the merge inputs is None: %s" % inputs)
 456   with ops.name_scope(name, "Merge", inputs) as name:
 457     inputs = [
 458         ops.internal_convert_to_tensor_or_indexed_slices(inp, as_ref=True)
 459         for inp in inputs
 460     ]
 461     if all([isinstance(v, ops.Tensor) for v in inputs]):
 462       if all([v.dtype._is_ref_dtype for v in inputs]):  # pylint: disable=protected-access
 463         return gen_control_flow_ops.ref_merge(inputs, name)
 464       else:
 465         return gen_control_flow_ops.merge(inputs, name)
 466     elif all([isinstance(v, sparse_tensor.SparseTensor) for v in inputs]):
 467       # Only handle the case when all inputs are SparseTensor.
 468       values, _ = merge([inp.values for inp in inputs], name=name)
 469       indices, chosen_index = gen_control_flow_ops.merge(
 470           [inp.indices for inp in inputs], name="indices")
 471       dense_shape, _ = gen_control_flow_ops.merge(
 472           [inp.dense_shape for inp in inputs], name="dense_shape")
 473       return (sparse_tensor.SparseTensor(indices, values, dense_shape),
 474               chosen_index)
 475     else:
 476       # For now convert all the inputs as IndexedSlices.
 477       inputs = math_ops._as_indexed_slices_list(inputs, optimize=False)
 478       values, _ = merge([inp.values for inp in inputs], name=name)
 479       indices, chosen_index = gen_control_flow_ops.merge(
 480           [inp.indices for inp in inputs], name="indices")
 481       if any(inp.dense_shape is not None for inp in inputs):
 482         if any(inp.dense_shape is None for inp in inputs):
 483           raise ValueError("Either all merged IndexedSlices must have a "
 484                            "dense_shape, or none must have a dense_shape.")
 485         dense_shape, _ = gen_control_flow_ops.merge(
 486             [inp.dense_shape for inp in inputs], name="dense_shape")
 487       else:
 488         dense_shape = None
 489       return ops.IndexedSlices(values, indices, dense_shape), chosen_index

 502 def _make_tensor_array(ta, t_or_flow):
 503   # pylint: disable=protected-access
 504   new_ta = tensor_array_ops.TensorArray(
 505       dtype=ta.dtype,
 506       handle=ta.handle,
 507       flow=t_or_flow,
 508       infer_shape=ta._infer_shape,
 509       colocate_with_first_write_call=ta._colocate_with_first_write_call)

 516 def _convert_flows_to_tensorarrays(tensors_or_tensorarrays, tensors_or_flows):
 517   if len(tensors_or_tensorarrays) != len(tensors_or_flows):
 518     raise ValueError(
 519         "Lengths of original Tensor list and new list do not match: %d vs. %d" %
 520         (len(tensors_or_tensorarrays), len(tensors_or_flows)))
 521   return [
 522       _make_tensor_array(ta, t_or_flow)
 523       if isinstance(ta, tensor_array_ops.TensorArray) else t_or_flow
 524       for (ta, t_or_flow) in zip(tensors_or_tensorarrays, tensors_or_flows)
 525   ]

 527 
 528 def _ShapeLessThanOrEqual(shape1, shape2):
 529   if shape2.dims is None:
 530     return True
 531   if shape1.ndims != shape2.ndims:
 532     return False
 533   for dim1, dim2 in zip(shape1.dims, shape2.dims):
 534     if dim2.value is not None and dim1.value != dim2.value:
 535       return False
 536   return True

 538 
 539 def _SetShapeInvariants(input_vars, enter_vars, shapes):
 540   """Set the shapes of the tensors in `enter_vars` to `shapes`.
 541 
 542   Args:
 543     input_vars: A list of tensors that are inputs to `enter_vars`.
 544     enter_vars: A list of tensors whose shapes will be set.
 545     shapes: A (possibly nested) list of shapes.
 546 
 547   Raises:
 548     ValueError: If any tensor in `enter_vars` has a less specific shape
 549       than its corresponding shape in `shapes`.
 550   """
 551   if shapes is None:
 552     return
 553   flat_shapes = nest.flatten(shapes)
 554   if not all([isinstance(s, tensor_shape.TensorShape) for s in flat_shapes]):
 555     raise ValueError("`shapes` must be a (possibly nested) list of shapes.")
 556   # Check that the shapes of the inputs are less than the shape invariants,
 557   # and set the shapes of `enter_vars` to the shape invariants.
 558   for inp, var, shape in zip(input_vars, enter_vars, flat_shapes):
 559     if isinstance(var, ops.Tensor):
 560       if not _ShapeLessThanOrEqual(inp.get_shape(), shape):
 561         raise ValueError(
 562             "The shape invariant specified for %s is not compatible with "
 563             "the initial shape of the loop variable. It enters the loop "
 564             "with shape %s, but the specified shape invariant is %s." %
 565             (inp.name, inp.get_shape(), shape))
 566       var.set_shape(shape)
 567     else:
 568       if not isinstance(var, (ops.IndexedSlices, sparse_tensor.SparseTensor)):
 569         raise TypeError("Type %s not supported" % type(var))
 570       if isinstance(var, ops.IndexedSlices):
 571         if not _ShapeLessThanOrEqual(inp.values.get_shape(), shape):
 572           raise ValueError(
 573               "The shape invariant specified for %s is not compatible with "
 574               "the initial shape of the values tensor of this IndexedSlices. "
 575               "It enters the loop with shape %s, but the specified shape "
 576               "invariant is %s." % (inp.values.name, inp.values.get_shape(),
 577                                     shape))
 578         var.values.set_shape(shape)
 579         var.indices.set_shape(tensor_shape.TensorShape([shape[0]]))
 580         if var.dense_shape is not None:
 581           var.dense_shape.set_shape(tensor_shape.TensorShape([shape.ndims]))
 582       else:
 583         if not _ShapeLessThanOrEqual(inp.dense_shape.get_shape(), shape):
 584           raise ValueError(
 585               "The shape invariant specified for %s is not compatible with "
 586               "the initial shape of the shape tensor of this SparseTensor. "
 587               "It enters the loop with shape %s, but the specified shape "
 588               "invariant is %s." % (inp.dense_shape.name,
 589                                     inp.dense_shape.get_shape(), shape))
 590         var.values.set_shape(tensor_shape.TensorShape([None]))
 591         var.indices.set_shape(tensor_shape.TensorShape([None, shape.ndims]))
 592         var.dense_shape.set_shape(shape)
 593 
 594 
 595 def _EnforceShapeInvariant(merge_var, next_var):
 596   """Check if the shapes of the loops variables are invariants.
 597 
 598   Args:
 599     merge_var: The list of tensors representing the initial values of the
 600       loop variables.
 601     next_var: The list of tensors representing the values of the loop
 602       variables after one loop iteration.
 603 
 604   Raises:
 605     ValueError: If any tensor in `merge_var` has a more specific shape than
 606       its correspnding tensor in `next_var`.
 607   """
 608   if isinstance(merge_var, ops.Tensor):
 609     m_shape = merge_var.get_shape()
 610     n_shape = next_var.get_shape()
 611     if not _ShapeLessThanOrEqual(n_shape, m_shape):
 612       enter = merge_var.op.inputs[0].op
 613       assert util.IsLoopEnter(enter)
 614       input_t = enter.inputs[0]
 615       raise ValueError(
 616           "Input tensor '%s' enters the loop with shape %s, but has shape %s "
 617           "after one iteration. To allow the shape to vary across iterations, "
 618           "use the `shape_invariants` argument of tf.while_loop to specify a "
 619           "less-specific shape." %
 620           (input_t.name, input_t.shape, n_shape))
 621   else:
 622     if not isinstance(merge_var,
 623                       (ops.IndexedSlices, sparse_tensor.SparseTensor)):
 624       raise TypeError("Type %s not supported" % type(merge_var))
 625     if isinstance(merge_var, ops.IndexedSlices):
 626       m_values_shape = merge_var.values.get_shape()
 627       m_indices_shape = merge_var.indices.get_shape()
 628       m_shape_shape = tensor_shape.TensorShape(None)
 629       if merge_var.dense_shape is not None:
 630         m_shape_shape = merge_var.dense_shape.get_shape()
 631       n_values_shape = next_var.values.get_shape()
 632       n_indices_shape = next_var.indices.get_shape()
 633       n_shape_shape = tensor_shape.TensorShape(None)
 634       if next_var.dense_shape is not None:
 635         n_shape_shape = next_var.dense_shape.get_shape()
 636       if (not _ShapeLessThanOrEqual(n_values_shape, m_values_shape) or
 637           not _ShapeLessThanOrEqual(n_indices_shape, m_indices_shape)):
 638         if not _ShapeLessThanOrEqual(n_values_shape, m_values_shape):
 639           raise ValueError(
 640               "The shape for %s is not an invariant for the loop. It enters "
 641               "the loop with shape (%s, %s, %s), but has shape (%s, %s, %s) "
 642               "after one iteration. Provide shape invariants using either the "
 643               "`shape_invariants` argument of tf.while_loop or set_shape() "
 644               "on the loop variables." %
 645               (merge_var.name, m_values_shape, m_indices_shape, m_shape_shape,
 646                n_values_shape, n_indices_shape, n_shape_shape))
 647     else:
 648       m_values_shape = merge_var.values.get_shape()
 649       m_indices_shape = merge_var.indices.get_shape()
 650       m_shape_shape = merge_var.dense_shape.get_shape()
 651       n_values_shape = next_var.values.get_shape()
 652       n_indices_shape = next_var.indices.get_shape()
 653       n_shape_shape = next_var.dense_shape.get_shape()
 654       if (not _ShapeLessThanOrEqual(n_values_shape, m_values_shape) or
 655           not _ShapeLessThanOrEqual(n_indices_shape, m_indices_shape) or
 656           not _ShapeLessThanOrEqual(n_shape_shape, m_shape_shape)):
 657         raise ValueError(
 658             "The shape for %s is not an invariant for the loop. It enters "
 659             "the loop with shape (%s, %s, %s), but has shape (%s, %s, %s) "
 660             "after one iteration. Provide shape invariants using either "
 661             "the `shape_invariants` argument of tf.while_loop or set_shape() "
 662             "on the loop variables." %
 663             (merge_var.name, m_values_shape, m_indices_shape, m_shape_shape,
 664              n_values_shape, n_indices_shape, n_shape_shape))
 665 
 666 
 667 def _AddNextAndBackEdge(m, v, enforce_shape_invariant=True):
 668   """Add NextIteration and back edge from v to m."""
 669   if isinstance(m, ops.Tensor):
 670     v = ops.convert_to_tensor(v)
 671     v = _NextIteration(v)
 672     if enforce_shape_invariant:
 673       # Make sure the shapes of loop outputs are correct. We do this before
 674       # calling _update_input, which will raise a less-helpful error message if
 675       # the types don't match.
 676       # TODO(skyewm): call this for other cases below (needs testing)
 677       _EnforceShapeInvariant(m, v)
 678     m.op._update_input(1, v)  # pylint: disable=protected-access
 679   elif isinstance(m, ops.IndexedSlices):
 680     # pylint: disable=protected-access
 681     v = math_ops._as_indexed_slices(v, optimize=False)
 682     v = _NextIteration(v)
 683     m.values.op._update_input(1, v.values)
 684     m.indices.op._update_input(1, v.indices)
 685     # pylint: enable=protected-access
 686     if m.dense_shape is not None:
 687       if v.dense_shape is None:
 688         raise ValueError("Must have dense shape: %s" % v.name)
 689       m.dense_shape.op._update_input(1, v.dense_shape)
 690   elif isinstance(m, sparse_tensor.SparseTensor):
 691     if not isinstance(v, sparse_tensor.SparseTensor):
 692       raise ValueError("Must be a sparse tensor: %s" % v.name)
 693     v = _NextIteration(v)
 694     # pylint: disable=protected-access
 695     m.values.op._update_input(1, v.values)
 696     m.indices.op._update_input(1, v.indices)
 697     m.dense_shape.op._update_input(1, v.dense_shape)
 698     # pylint: enable=protected-access
 699   else:
 700     raise TypeError("Type %s not supported" % type(m))
 701   return v
 702

 704 def GetMaxSizeFromNestedMaximumIterations(value, while_ctxt):
 705   """Calculate a max_size for use by stack ops inside an XLA while_loop.
 706 
 707   Args:
 708     value: The value inside the while_loop forward context.  Used for printing
 709       error messages.
 710     while_ctxt: The forward context inside which value resides.  This does
 711       not always match the value's immediate context, as `value` may be
 712       inside e.g. a cond context inside the while_loop.
 713 
 714   Returns:
 715     A tensor containing the `max_size` to feed to a Stack initializer.
 716 
 717   Raises:
 718     ValueError: If `value` is nested inside a `while_loop` that either
 719       lacks a `maximum_iterations` parameter, or the `maximum_iterations`
 720       parameter:
 721 
 722         - is inside a `while_loop` that is a parent of the calling context, and
 723         - cannot be evaluated at graph build time to a constant.
 724   """
 725   value_name = value.name
 726   # curr_ctxt is the context that tf.gradients was called in.
 727   curr_ctxt = ops.get_default_graph()._get_control_flow_context()  # pylint: disable=protected-access
 728 
 729   curr_ctxt_name = curr_ctxt.name if curr_ctxt is not None else ""
 730   max_size = constant_op.constant(1)
 731 
 732   # Loop through all containing while contexts between value and the
 733   # current context, multiplying together each context's
 734   # max_iterations to get the maximum stack size.
 735   while while_ctxt not in (None, curr_ctxt):
 736     max_iter = while_ctxt.maximum_iterations
 737     if max_iter is None:
 738       raise ValueError(
 739           "Cannot create a gradient accumulator for tensor '%s' inside "
 740           "XLA while_loop because maximum_iterations was not passed to "
 741           "the tf.while_loop call ('%s')." % (value_name, while_ctxt.name))
 742 
 743     # pylint: disable=protected-access
 744     max_iter_ctxt = max_iter.op._get_control_flow_context()
 745     # pylint: enable=protected-access
 746 
 747     # If max_iter_ctxt (non-strictly) contains curr_ctxt, then it's OK to use.
 748     if util.IsContainingContext(curr_ctxt, max_iter_ctxt):
 749       max_size *= max_iter
 750     else:
 751       # We cannot use max_iter because it's defined in a nested while
 752       # or cond context, so will fail if we try to use it as input to
 753       # any ops in curr_ctxt (e.g. max_size or the final accumulator
 754       # stack). Attempt to get a constant value out to use instead.
 755       const_max_iter = tensor_util.constant_value(max_iter)
 756       if const_max_iter is None:
 757         raise ValueError(
 758             "Cannot create a gradient accumulator for tensor '%s' inside XLA "
 759             "while_loop. maximum_iterations tensor '%s' for while_loop context "
 760             "'%s' must be statically known (e.g. a constant value or known "
 761             "shape dimension), or be defined at or outside the while loop "
 762             "context '%s' (currently defined in '%s')." %
 763             (value_name, max_iter.name, while_ctxt.name, curr_ctxt_name,
 764              max_iter_ctxt.name))
 765       max_size *= const_max_iter
 766 
 767     # Find the next outer WhileContext (or stop if we reach the
 768     # tf.gradient's context).
 769     while_ctxt = util.GetContainingWhileContext(
 770         while_ctxt.outer_context, stop_ctxt=curr_ctxt)
 771 
 772   return max_size
 773 
 774 
 775 class GradLoopState(object):
 776   """The state used for constructing the gradient graph for a while loop.
 777 
 778   We create a GradLoopState for each while loop in forward and its
 779   corresponding while loop in backprop. This gives us access to both
 780   the forward and the backprop WhileContexts.
 781 
 782   During the construction of gradient graph, any time when we detect
 783   a forward value that is needed for backprop, we create a history
 784   accumulator and add it to `history_map`. Any time when we backprop
 785   a loop switch op (in _SwitchGrad), we add the grad merge op in
 786   `switch_map`.
 787   """
 788 
 789   def __init__(self, forward_ctxt, outer_grad_state):
 790     # The grad loop state for the outer while loop.
 791     self._outer_grad_state = None
 792 
 793     # The while loop context for forward.
 794     self._forward_context = None
 795 
 796     # The loop counter added by AddForwardLoopCounter. It is the value
 797     # of the loop counter for the next iteration.
 798     self._forward_index = None
 799 
 800     # A sync op for forward.
 801     self._forward_sync = None
 802 
 803     # The while loop context for backprop.
 804     self._grad_context = None
 805 
 806     # The loop counter added by AddBackpropLoopCounter. It is the value
 807     # of the loop counter for the current iteration.
 808     self._grad_index = None
 809 
 810     # A sync op for backprop.
 811     self._grad_sync = None
 812 
 813     # Information needed by backprop.
 814     self._history_map = {}
 815     self._switch_map = {}
 816     self._unused_exits = []
 817     self._deferred_exits = []
 818     self._forward_loop_exits = list(forward_ctxt.loop_exits)
 819     self._pending_exits_count = len(forward_ctxt.loop_exits)
 820 
 821     self._outer_grad_state = outer_grad_state
 822     if outer_grad_state:
 823       outer_forward_ctxt = outer_grad_state.forward_context
 824     else:
 825       if not hasattr(forward_ctxt, "outer_context"):
 826         raise ValueError("Failed to call gradients on a while loop without"
 827                          "properly serializing graph via MetaGraphDef")
 828       outer_forward_ctxt = forward_ctxt.outer_context
 829 
 830     # Add the forward loop counter.
 831     with forward_ctxt._graph.as_default():  # pylint: disable=protected-access
 832       if outer_forward_ctxt:
 833         outer_forward_ctxt.Enter()
 834       cnt, forward_index = forward_ctxt.AddForwardLoopCounter(outer_grad_state)
 835       if outer_forward_ctxt:
 836         outer_forward_ctxt.Exit()
 837     self._forward_context = forward_ctxt
 838     self._forward_index = forward_index
 839 
 840     # Add the backprop WhileContext, and the backprop loop counter.
 841     if outer_grad_state:
 842       # This is a nested loop. Remember the iteration counts for each
 843       # execution of this inner loop.
 844       outer_forward_ctxt.AddName(cnt.name)
 845       history_cnt = outer_grad_state.AddForwardAccumulator(cnt)
 846 
 847       outer_grad_ctxt = outer_grad_state.grad_context
 848       outer_grad_ctxt.Enter()
 849       self._grad_context = WhileContext(
 850           maximum_iterations=forward_ctxt.maximum_iterations,
 851           parallel_iterations=forward_ctxt.parallel_iterations,
 852           back_prop=forward_ctxt.back_prop,
 853           swap_memory=forward_ctxt.swap_memory,
 854           name=forward_ctxt.name,
 855           grad_state=self)
 856       real_cnt = outer_grad_state.AddBackpropAccumulatedValue(history_cnt, cnt)
 857       self._grad_index = self._grad_context.AddBackpropLoopCounter(
 858           real_cnt, outer_grad_state)
 859       outer_grad_ctxt.Exit()
 860     else:
 861       if outer_forward_ctxt:
 862         outer_forward_ctxt.Enter()
 863       self._grad_context = WhileContext(
 864           maximum_iterations=forward_ctxt.maximum_iterations,
 865           parallel_iterations=forward_ctxt.parallel_iterations,
 866           back_prop=forward_ctxt.back_prop,
 867           swap_memory=forward_ctxt.swap_memory,
 868           name=forward_ctxt.name,
 869           grad_state=self)
 870       self._grad_index = self._grad_context.AddBackpropLoopCounter(
 871           cnt, outer_grad_state)
 872       if outer_forward_ctxt:
 873         outer_forward_ctxt.Exit()
 874

 890   @property
 891   def forward_sync(self):
 892     """A control trigger node for synchronization in the forward loop.
 893 
 894     One main use is to keep the push ops of a stack executed in the
 895     iteration order.
 896     """
 897     if self._forward_sync is None:
 898       with ops.control_dependencies(None):
 899         self._forward_sync = control_trigger(name="f_sync")
 900       self._forward_sync._set_control_flow_context(self._forward_context)
 901       self._forward_index.op._add_control_input(self._forward_sync)
 902     return self._forward_sync

 915   def grad_sync(self):
 916     """A control trigger node for synchronization in the grad loop.
 917 
 918     One main use is to keep the pop ops of a stack executed in the
 919     iteration order.
 920     """
 921     if self._grad_sync is None:
 922       with ops.control_dependencies(None):
 923         self._grad_sync = control_trigger(name="b_sync")
 924       self._grad_sync._set_control_flow_context(self._grad_context)
 925       self._grad_index.op._add_control_input(self._grad_sync)
 926       if self._grad_context.outer_context:
 927         self._grad_context.outer_context.AddInnerOp(self._grad_sync)

 964 
 965   def AddForwardAccumulator(self, value, dead_branch=False):
 966     """Add an accumulator for each forward tensor that is needed in backprop.
 967 
 968     This is added to the forward loop at the first time when a tensor
 969     in the forward loop is used by backprop gradient computation loop.
 970     We create an accumulator that accumulates the value of tensor at each
 971     iteration. Called in the control flow context where gradients() is called.
 972 
 973     The pseudocode is:
 974     ```
 975       acc = stack();
 976       while (_pivot) {
 977         acc = stack_push(acc, value);
 978       }
 979     ```
 980 
 981     We make sure that the stack push op in one iteration is executed before
 982     next iteration. This is achieved by adding a control edge from
 983     `forward_index.op.inputs[0].op` to the push op, and another control
 984     edge from the push op to either `forward_index.op` or `forward_sync`.
 985 
 986     Args:
 987       value: The source tensor in forward that is to be accumulated.
 988       dead_branch: True iff the tensor is on a dead branch of a cond.
 989 
 990     Returns:
 991       The stack that contains the accumulated history of the tensor.
 992 
 993     Raises:
 994       TypeError: For internal errors involving the value condition context.
 995       ValueError: If `value` is inside a XLA scope and a valid max size
 996         for the stack can't be found.
 997     """
 998     # curr_ctxt is the context that tf.gradients was called in.
 999     with self._forward_index.graph.as_default():
1000       curr_ctxt = ops.get_default_graph()._get_control_flow_context()  # pylint: disable=protected-access
1001       with ops.control_dependencies(None):
1002         if curr_ctxt:
1003           curr_ctxt.Enter()
1004         with ops.colocate_with(value):
1005           # We only need to pass maximum_iterations to the stack if
1006           # we're inside an XLA context.
1007           if not util.IsInXLAContext(value.op):
1008             max_size = constant_op.constant(-1, dtypes.int32)
1009           else:
1010             max_size = GetMaxSizeFromNestedMaximumIterations(
1011                 value, self.forward_context)
1012           acc = gen_data_flow_ops.stack_v2(
1013               max_size=max_size, elem_type=value.dtype.base_dtype, name="f_acc")
1014         if curr_ctxt:
1015           curr_ctxt.Exit()
1016 
1017         # Make acc available in the forward context.
1018         enter_acc = self.forward_context.AddValue(acc)
1019 
1020         # Add the stack_push op in the context of value.op.
1021         swap_enabled = self.forward_context.swap_memory
1022         value_ctxt = util.GetOutputContext(value.op)
1023         if value_ctxt == self.forward_context:
1024           # value is not nested in the forward context.
1025           self.forward_context.Enter()
1026           push = gen_data_flow_ops.stack_push_v2(
1027               enter_acc, value, swap_memory=swap_enabled)
1028           self.forward_context.Exit()
1029           # Protect stack push and order it before forward_index.
1030           self.forward_index.op._add_control_input(push.op)
1031         else:
1032           # value is in a cond context within the forward context.
1033           if not isinstance(value_ctxt, CondContext):
1034             raise TypeError("value_ctxt is not a CondContext: %s" % value_ctxt)
1035           if dead_branch:
1036             # The special case for creating a zero tensor for a dead
1037             # branch of a switch. See ControlFlowState.ZerosLike().
1038             value_ctxt.outer_context.Enter()
1039             push = gen_data_flow_ops.stack_push_v2(
1040                 enter_acc, value, swap_memory=swap_enabled)
1041             value_ctxt.outer_context.Exit()
1042             push.op._set_control_flow_context(value_ctxt)
1043           else:
1044             value_ctxt.Enter()
1045             push = gen_data_flow_ops.stack_push_v2(
1046                 enter_acc, value, swap_memory=swap_enabled)
1047             value_ctxt.Exit()
1048           # Protect stack push and order it before forward_sync.
1049           self.forward_sync._add_control_input(push.op)
1050         # Order stack push after the successor of forward_index
1051         add_op = self.forward_index.op.inputs[0].op
1052         push.op._add_control_input(add_op)
1053         return acc
1054 
1055   def AddBackpropAccumulatedValue(self, history_value, value,
1056                                   dead_branch=False):
1057     """Add the getter for an accumulated value in the grad context.
1058 
1059     This is added to the backprop loop. Called in the grad context to
1060     get the value of an accumulated value. The stack pop op must be guarded
1061     by the pred of the controlling cond.
1062 
1063     Args:
1064       history_value: The history (a stack) of a value.
1065       value: The value that is pushed onto the stack.
1066       dead_branch: True iff the tensor is on a dead branch of a cond.
1067 
1068     Returns:
1069       The current value (the top of the stack).
1070     """
1071     history_ctxt = history_value.op._get_control_flow_context()
1072     # Find the cond context that controls history_value if any.
1073     cond_ctxt = None
1074     value_ctxt = value.op._get_control_flow_context()
1075     while value_ctxt and value_ctxt != history_ctxt:
1076       if isinstance(value_ctxt, CondContext):
1077         cond_ctxt = value_ctxt
1078         break
1079       value_ctxt = value_ctxt.outer_context
1080     with ops.control_dependencies(None):
1081       self.grad_context.Enter()
1082       if cond_ctxt:
1083         # Guard stack pop with a switch if it is controlled by a cond.
1084         grad_state = self
1085         pred = None
1086         while pred is None and grad_state:
1087           pred = grad_state.history_map.get(cond_ctxt.pred.name)
1088           grad_state = grad_state.outer_grad_state
1089         if pred is None:
1090           pred = cond_ctxt.pred
1091         branch = (1 - cond_ctxt.branch) if dead_branch else cond_ctxt.branch
1092         history_value = _SwitchRefOrTensor(history_value, pred)[branch]
1093       pop = gen_data_flow_ops.stack_pop_v2(history_value,
1094                                            value.dtype.base_dtype)
1095       pop.set_shape(value.get_shape())
1096       self.grad_context.Exit()
1097     parallel_iterations = self.grad_context.parallel_iterations
1098     if parallel_iterations > 1:
1099       # All pops are ordered after pivot_for_body and before grad_sync.
1100       self.grad_sync._add_control_input(pop.op)
1101     return pop
1102 
1103   def GetRealValue(self, value):
1104     """Get the real value of `value`.
1105 
1106     If backprop "uses" a value produced by forward inference, an accumulator
1107     is added in the forward loop to accumulate its values.  We use the
1108     accumulated value. This method must be called in the grad loop context.
1109     `value` must be in forward and needed for backprop.
1110 
1111     Args:
1112       value: A tensor to be captured.
1113 
1114     Returns:
1115       The same tensor obtained from the saved history.
1116     """
1117     assert value.op.type not in ["Variable", "VariableV2"]
1118     real_value = self._history_map.get(value.name)
1119     if real_value is None:
1120       cur_value = value
1121       cur_grad_state = self
1122       while True:
1123         enter_op = util.GetLoopConstantEnter(cur_value)
1124         if enter_op:
1125           # Special case: cur_value comes from a constant Enter node.
1126           cur_value = enter_op.inputs[0]
1127           cur_grad_state = cur_grad_state.outer_grad_state
1128           if cur_grad_state is None:
1129             # We are now outside all nested loops for this gradient(),
1130             # so `value` is a loop invariant and there is no need to
1131             # save the history of value. Just make cur_value to enter
1132             # the right control flow context.
1133             real_value = self._grad_context.AddValue(cur_value)
1134             break
1135         elif constant_op.is_constant(cur_value):
1136           # If the value to be forwarded is a constant, clone the constant in
1137           # the gradient loop rather than using a stack.
1138           # TODO(phawkins): consider hoisting the constant out of the loop
1139           # instead.
1140           real_value = constant_op.constant(
1141               tensor_util.constant_value(cur_value), dtype=cur_value.dtype)
1142           break
1143         else:
1144           # Record the history of this value in forward_ctxt.
1145           self._grad_context.Exit()
1146           history_value = cur_grad_state.AddForwardAccumulator(cur_value)
1147           self._grad_context.Enter()
1148           break
1149 
1150       if real_value is None:
1151         # Add the stack pop op in the grad context.
1152         real_value = cur_grad_state.AddBackpropAccumulatedValue(
1153             history_value, cur_value)
1154         if cur_grad_state != self:
1155           real_value = self._grad_context.AddValue(real_value)
1156       self._history_map[value.name] = real_value
1157     return real_value
1158

1160 def _GetWhileContext(op):
1161   """Get the WhileContext to which this op belongs."""
1162   ctxt = op._get_control_flow_context()
1163   if ctxt:
1164     ctxt = ctxt.GetWhileContext()
1165   return ctxt

1168 class ControlFlowState(object):
1169   """Maintain the mapping from the loops to their grad states."""
1170 
1171   def __init__(self):
1172     self._map = {}  # maps forward loop context to GradLoopState
1173 
1174   def GetGradState(self, op, before):
1175     """Return the grad state for this op if it's in a forward loop context."""
1176     if before and util.IsLoopExit(op):
1177       forward_ctxt = op._get_control_flow_context()
1178       forward_ctxt = forward_ctxt.outer_context
1179       if forward_ctxt:
1180         forward_ctxt = forward_ctxt.GetWhileContext()
1181     else:
1182       forward_ctxt = _GetWhileContext(op)
1183     if forward_ctxt:
1184       return self._map.get(forward_ctxt)
1185     return None
1186 
1187   def ProcessUnusedLoopExits(self, pending_count, to_ops_set):
1188     """Process all the "unused" loop exits.
1189 
1190     The "unused" exits of the loops are added to `unused_exits`. An exit is
1191     unused if its pending_count is 0. If there is an exit with real gradient,
1192     all these deferred exits will enter the backprop loop with zero gradient.
1193     Otherwise, they will enter the backprop loop with None. As an example,
1194     people often write:
1195 
1196     ```python
1197     v1, _ = tf.while_loop(p, b, [x1, x2])
1198     result = gradients(v1, x1)
1199     ```
1200 
1201     The exit node for x2 is not included by the betweenness analysis. But we
1202     need to backprop x2 if x2 is involved in computing v1.
1203 
1204     Args:
1205       pending_count: The number of backprop inputs for every op.
1206       to_ops_set: The set of ops for ys in gradients(ys, xs)
1207 
1208     Returns:
1209       The set of unused loop exits that we know at this point we need
1210       to backprop.
1211     """
1212     loop_exits = []
1213     for grad_state in self._map.values():
1214       for y in grad_state.forward_loop_exits:
1215         if pending_count[y.op] == 0:
1216           grad_state.pending_exits_count -= 1
1217           if y.op not in to_ops_set:
1218             grad_state.unused_exits.append(y)
1219           if grad_state.pending_exits_count == 0:
1220             loop_exits.extend(grad_state.unused_exits)
1221       # Need to include Enters in backprop for higher-order gradients.
1222       for y in grad_state.forward_context.loop_enters:
1223         if pending_count[y.op] == 0:
1224           pending_count[y.op] = 1
1225     return loop_exits
1226 
1227   def EnterGradWhileContext(self, op, before):
1228     """Enter the WhileContext for gradient computation."""
1229     grad_state = self.GetGradState(op, before)
1230     if grad_state:
1231       grad_state.grad_context.Enter()
1232 
1233   def ExitGradWhileContext(self, op, before):
1234     """Exit the WhileContext for gradient computation."""
1235     grad_state = self.GetGradState(op, before)
1236     if grad_state:
1237       grad_state.grad_context.Exit()
1238 
1239   def AddWhileContext(self, op, between_op_list, between_ops):
1240     """Add the grad state for the while loop that op belongs to.
1241 
1242     Note that op is an Exit, and this method must be called in
1243     the control flow context where gradients() is called.
1244 
1245     Note that this method modifies `between_op_list` and `between_ops`.
1246     """
1247     forward_ctxt = _GetWhileContext(op)
1248     grad_state = self._map.get(forward_ctxt)
1249     if grad_state is None:
1250       # This is a new while loop so create a grad state for it.
1251       outer_forward_ctxt = forward_ctxt.outer_context
1252       if outer_forward_ctxt:
1253         outer_forward_ctxt = outer_forward_ctxt.GetWhileContext()
1254       outer_grad_state = None
1255       if outer_forward_ctxt:
1256         outer_grad_state = self._map.get(outer_forward_ctxt)
1257       grad_state = GradLoopState(forward_ctxt, outer_grad_state)
1258       self._map[forward_ctxt] = grad_state
1259 
1260       # We need to include all exits of a loop for backprop.
1261       for loop_exit in grad_state.forward_loop_exits:
1262         if loop_exit.op not in between_ops:
1263           between_ops.add(loop_exit.op)
1264           between_op_list.append(loop_exit.op)
1265 
1266   def ZerosLikeForExit(self, val):
1267     """Create zeros_like gradient for a loop exit.
1268 
1269     If the result of a loop variable is not used but is involved in
1270     computing the result of some needed loop variable, we create a
1271     zero-valued tensor that is fed as gradient for the Exit node of that
1272     loop variable. Note that val.op is an Exit, and this method must be
1273     called in the control flow context where gradients() is called.
1274 
1275     Args:
1276       val: The output tensor of an Exit op.
1277 
1278     Returns:
1279       A zero tensor of the same shape of val.
1280     """
1281     val_shape = val.get_shape()
1282     forward_ctxt = val.op._get_control_flow_context()
1283     outer_forward_ctxt = forward_ctxt.outer_context
1284     if outer_forward_ctxt:
1285       outer_forward_ctxt = outer_forward_ctxt.GetWhileContext()
1286     outer_grad_state = None
1287     if outer_forward_ctxt:
1288       outer_grad_state = self._map.get(outer_forward_ctxt)
1289     if outer_grad_state:
1290       # This is a nested loop.
1291       if val_shape.is_fully_defined():
1292         # If the shape is known statically, just create a zero tensor
1293         # with the right shape in the right context.
1294         outer_grad_state.grad_context.Enter()
1295         result = array_ops.zeros(val_shape.dims, val.dtype)
1296         outer_grad_state.grad_context.Exit()
1297       else:
1298         # Only the shape of value is needed for backprop.
1299         forward_ctxt.outer_context.Enter()
1300         shape = array_ops.shape_internal(val, optimize=False)
1301         forward_ctxt.outer_context.Exit()
1302         # Save the shape to a stack.
1303         history_shape = outer_grad_state.AddForwardAccumulator(shape)
1304         # Get the shape back from the stack.
1305         outer_grad_ctxt = outer_grad_state.grad_context
1306         outer_grad_ctxt.Enter()
1307         real_shape = outer_grad_state.AddBackpropAccumulatedValue(
1308             history_shape, shape)
1309         result = array_ops.zeros(real_shape, val.dtype)
1310         outer_grad_ctxt.Exit()
1311     else:
1312       # This is not a nested loop.
1313       if val_shape.is_fully_defined():
1314         # If the shape is known statically, just create a zero tensor
1315         # with the right shape.
1316         result = array_ops.zeros(val_shape.dims, val.dtype)
1317       else:
1318         result = array_ops.zeros_like(val, optimize=False)
1319     return result
1320 
1321   def ZerosLike(self, op, index):
1322     """Create zeros_like for the specified output of an op.
1323 
1324     If op is in a while loop that is part of gradients(), this method
1325     must be called in its grad loop context.
1326 
1327     Args:
1328       op: A tensorflow operation.
1329       index: the index for a specific output of the op.
1330 
1331     Returns:
1332       A zero tensor of the same shape of op.outputs[index].
1333     """
1334     if util.IsLoopSwitch(op):
1335       return None
1336     dead_branch = util.IsSwitch(op)
1337     forward_ctxt = _GetWhileContext(op)
1338     grad_state = self._map.get(forward_ctxt)
1339     if grad_state is None:
1340       # op is not in a while loop that is part of gradients().
1341       return ZerosLikeOutsideLoop(op, index)
1342     op_ctxt = op._get_control_flow_context()
1343     val = ops.convert_to_tensor(op.outputs[index], name="tensor")
1344     shape = val.get_shape()
1345     if shape.is_fully_defined():
1346       # If the shape is known statically, just create a zero tensor with
1347       # the right shape in the grad loop context.
1348       result = constant_op.constant(0, shape=shape.dims, dtype=val.dtype)
1349       if dead_branch:
1350         # op is a cond switch. Guard the zero tensor with a switch.
1351         pred = grad_state.history_map.get(op_ctxt.pred.name)
1352         branch = op_ctxt.branch
1353         result = _SwitchRefOrTensor(result, pred)[1 - branch]
1354     else:
1355       # Unknown shape so keep a history of the shape at runtime.
1356       if dead_branch:
1357         # Need to add a special switch to guard the value.
1358         pred = op_ctxt.pred
1359         branch = op_ctxt.branch
1360         op_ctxt.outer_context.Enter()
1361         val = _SwitchRefOrTensor(op.inputs[0], pred)[1 - branch]
1362         zeros_shape = array_ops.shape_internal(val, optimize=False)
1363         op_ctxt.outer_context.Exit()
1364         val.op._set_control_flow_context(op_ctxt)
1365         zeros_shape.op._set_control_flow_context(op_ctxt)
1366       else:
1367         op_ctxt.Enter()
1368         zeros_shape = array_ops.shape_internal(val, optimize=False)
1369         op_ctxt.Exit()
1370 
1371       # Add forward accumulator for shape.
1372       grad_state.grad_context.Exit()
1373       history_zeros_shape = grad_state.AddForwardAccumulator(
1374           zeros_shape, dead_branch=dead_branch)
1375       grad_state.grad_context.Enter()
1376 
1377       # Create a zero tensor with the right shape.
1378       shape = grad_state.AddBackpropAccumulatedValue(history_zeros_shape,
1379                                                      zeros_shape, dead_branch)
1380       result = array_ops.zeros(shape, val.dtype)
1381     return result
1382 
1383   def PostProcessing(self):
1384     """Perform postprocessing at the end of gradients().
1385 
1386     We have created the gradient graph at this point. So this function
1387     can be used to perform any postprocessing on the gradient graph.
1388     We currently perform the following postprocessing:
1389       1. Patch the gradient graph if the output of a loop variable
1390          doesn't depend on its input.
1391     """
1392     for _, grad_state in self._map.items():
1393       for _, b_merge in grad_state.switch_map.items():
1394         if b_merge.op.inputs[0] == b_merge.op.inputs[1]:
1395           # The value of this loop variable at iteration i+1 doesn't
1396           # depend on its value at iteration i. So use zeros as the
1397           # gradients for all iterations > 0.
1398           dtype = b_merge.op.inputs[0].dtype
1399           shape = b_merge.op.inputs[0].get_shape()
1400           # pylint: disable=protected-access
1401           if shape.is_fully_defined():
1402             grad_state.grad_context.Enter()
1403             # Create a zeros and use it for iterations > 0.
1404             grad_val = constant_op.constant(0, dtype=dtype, shape=shape)
1405             next_grad_val = _NextIteration(grad_val)
1406             grad_state.grad_context.Exit()
1407           else:
1408             # Create a zeros in the outer grad context.
1409             outer_grad_ctxt = grad_state.grad_context.outer_context
1410             if outer_grad_ctxt:
1411               outer_grad_ctxt.Enter()
1412             enter_grad_op = b_merge.op.inputs[0].op
1413             enter_grad = enter_grad_op.inputs[0]
1414             grad_shape = array_ops.shape_internal(enter_grad, optimize=False)
1415             grad_val = array_ops.zeros(grad_shape)
1416             if outer_grad_ctxt:
1417               outer_grad_ctxt.Exit()
1418             # Use the zeros for iterations > 0.
1419             grad_state.grad_context.Enter()
1420             next_grad_val = _NextIteration(grad_val)
1421             grad_state.grad_context.Exit()
1422           b_merge.op._update_input(1, next_grad_val)
1423           # pylint: enable=protected-access
1424 
1425 
1426 def MaybeCreateControlFlowState(between_op_list, between_ops,
1427                                 colocate_gradients_with_ops):
1428   """Create the state for all the while loops involved in one gradients().
1429 
1430   We create a ControlFlowState when there are while loops involved in
1431   gradients(). In gradients(), control flow logic is only invoked when
1432   the ControlFlowState is not None.
1433 
1434   Note that this method modifies `between_op_list` and `between_ops`.
1435   """
1436   loop_state = None
1437   for op in between_op_list:
1438     if util.IsLoopExit(op):
1439       if loop_state is None:
1440         loop_state = ControlFlowState()
1441       if colocate_gradients_with_ops:
1442         with ops.colocate_with(op):
1443           loop_state.AddWhileContext(op, between_op_list, between_ops)
1444       else:
1445         loop_state.AddWhileContext(op, between_op_list, between_ops)
1446   return loop_state
1447 
1448 
1449 def ZerosLikeOutsideLoop(op, index):
1450   """Create zeros_like for the specified output of an op."""
1451   val = op.outputs[index]
1452   if not util.IsSwitch(op):
1453     if val.dtype == dtypes.resource:
1454       return array_ops.zeros(gen_resource_variable_ops.variable_shape(val))
1455     return array_ops.zeros_like(val, optimize=False)
1456   else:
1457     op_ctxt = op._get_control_flow_context()
1458     if op_ctxt:
1459       # We are in a cond context. Use a switch to create zeros only when needed.
1460       pred = op_ctxt.pred
1461       branch = op_ctxt.branch
1462       switch_val = switch(op.inputs[0], pred)[1 - branch]
1463       # A op is created along the branch taken as control dependencies are on
1464       # the whole op and not on the tensor output.
1465       pivot = array_ops.identity(switch_val)
1466       if val.dtype == dtypes.resource:
1467         with ops.control_dependencies([pivot]):
1468           return array_ops.zeros(
1469               gen_resource_variable_ops.variable_shape(switch_val))
1470       zeros_shape = array_ops.shape_internal(switch_val, optimize=False)
1471       # Ensure ops created within array_ops.zeros are dominated by switch in
1472       # cond context.
1473       with ops.control_dependencies([pivot]):
1474         return array_ops.zeros(zeros_shape, dtype=val.dtype)
1475     else:
1476       return array_ops.zeros_like(val, optimize=False)

1478 
1479 class ControlFlowContext(object):
1480   """The base class for control flow context.
1481 
1482   The usage pattern is a sequence of (Enter, Exit) followed by a final
1483   ExitResult.
1484 
1485   We maintain the following state for control flow contexts during graph
1486   construction:
1487    1. graph has _control_flow_context: the current context used to
1488       construct new nodes. Changed by ctxt.Enter() and ctxt.Exit()
1489    2. op has _control_flow_context: the context to which the op belongs.
1490       Set at the time the op is created. Immutable.
1491    3. A ControlFlowContext has _outer_context: the context in which this
1492       context is created. Set at the time a context is created. Immutable.
1493    4. A ControlFlowContext has _context_stack.
1494       Pushed and popped by ctxt.Enter() and ctxt.Exit()
1495   """
1496 
1497   def __init__(self, values_def=None, import_scope=None):
1498     self._nested_contexts = []
1499     self._outer_context = ops.get_default_graph()._get_control_flow_context()
1500     if self._outer_context:
1501       self._outer_context._nested_contexts.append(self)  # pylint: disable=protected-access
1502     self._context_stack = []
1503     if values_def:
1504       self._init_values_from_proto(values_def, import_scope=import_scope)
1505     else:
1506       # The names of tensors that have been already seen in this context.
1507       self._values = set()
1508       # The keys are the names of tensors referenced by but external to this
1509       # context. Each value is the Tensor that should be used by this context to
1510       # access the key value (e.g. a switch output guarding a cond input value).
1511       self._external_values = {}
1512 
1513   def _init_values_from_proto(self, values_def, import_scope=None):
1514     """Initializes values and external_values from `ValuesDef` protocol buffer.
1515 
1516     Args:
1517       values_def: `ValuesDef` protocol buffer.
1518       import_scope: Optional `string`. Name scope to add.
1519     """
1520     assert isinstance(values_def, control_flow_pb2.ValuesDef)
1521     self._values = set(
1522         ops.prepend_name_scope(value, import_scope)
1523         for value in values_def.values)
1524     g = ops.get_default_graph()
1525     self._external_values = {}
1526     for k, v in values_def.external_values.items():
1527       k = ops.prepend_name_scope(k, import_scope)
1528       self._external_values[k] = g.as_graph_element(
1529           ops.prepend_name_scope(v, import_scope))
1530     op_names = set([
1531         op.split(":")[0]
1532         for op in self._values - set(self._external_values.keys())
1533     ])
1534     for op in op_names:
1535       # pylint: disable=protected-access
1536       g.as_graph_element(op)._set_control_flow_context(self)
1537       # pylint: enable=protected-access
1538 
1539   @property
1540   def name(self):
1541     return self._name
1542 
1543   @property
1544   def outer_context(self):
1545     """Return the context containing this context."""
1546     return self._outer_context
1547 
1548   @property
1549   def grad_state(self):
1550     raise NotImplementedError("Abstract method")
1551 
1552   @property
1553   def back_prop(self):
1554     raise NotImplementedError("Abstract method")
1555 
1556   @abc.abstractmethod
1557   def to_control_flow_context_def(self, context_def, export_scope=None):
1558     """Serializes this into `context_def`.
1559 
1560     Args:
1561       context_def: a `ControlFlowContextDef` protocol buffer.
1562       export_scope: Optional `string`. Name scope to remove.
1563     """
1564     raise NotImplementedError("Abstract method")
1565 
1566   def _to_values_def(self, export_scope=None):
1567     """Converts the values to a `ValuesDef` protocol buffer.
1568 
1569     Args:
1570       export_scope: Optional `string`. Name scope to remove.
1571 
1572     Returns:
1573       A `ValuesDef` protocol buffer.
1574     """
1575     values_def = control_flow_pb2.ValuesDef()
1576     values_def.values.extend(
1577         [ops.strip_name_scope(v, export_scope) for v in sorted(self._values)])
1578     for k, v in self._external_values.items():
1579       k = ops.strip_name_scope(k, export_scope)
1580       values_def.external_values[k] = ops.strip_name_scope(v.name, export_scope)
1581     return values_def
1582 
1583   def AddName(self, name):
1584     self._values.add(name)
1585 
1586   # pylint: disable=protected-access
1587   def Enter(self):
1588     """Enter this control flow context."""
1589     graph = ops.get_default_graph()
1590     self._context_stack.append(graph._get_control_flow_context())
1591     graph._set_control_flow_context(self)
1592 
1593   def Exit(self):
1594     """Exit this control flow context."""
1595     graph = ops.get_default_graph()
1596     last_context = self._context_stack.pop()
1597     graph._set_control_flow_context(last_context)
1598 
1599   def EnterGradientColocation(self, op, gradient_uid):
1600     """Start building a gradient colocated with an op."""
1601     if self._outer_context:
1602       self._outer_context.EnterGradientColocation(op, gradient_uid)

1609   def ExitResult(self, result):
1610     """Make a list of tensors available in the outer context."""
1611     if self._outer_context:
1612       nest.map_structure(lambda x: self._outer_context.AddName(x.name), result)

1614   def GetWhileContext(self):
1615     """Return the while context containing this context."""
1616     if self._outer_context:
1617       return self._outer_context.GetWhileContext()
1618     return None

1620   def _IsInOuterContext(self, op):
1621     op_ctxt = util.GetOutputContext(op)
1622     outer_ctxt = self.outer_context
1623     while outer_ctxt != op_ctxt:
1624       if outer_ctxt is None:
1625         return False
1626       outer_ctxt = outer_ctxt.outer_context
1627     return True
1628 
1629   def _RemoveExternalControlEdges(self, op):
1630     """Remove any external control dependency on this op."""
1631     while_ctxt = self.GetWhileContext()
1632     # A control input of `op` is internal if it is in the same while
1633     # loop context as the enclosing while loop context of self.
1634     if while_ctxt is None:
1635       internal_control_inputs = op.control_inputs
1636     else:
1637       internal_control_inputs = []
1638       for x in op.control_inputs:
1639         ctxt = util.GetOutputContext(x)
1640         if ctxt is not None and ctxt.GetWhileContext() == while_ctxt:
1641           internal_control_inputs.append(x)
1642     external_control_inputs = []
1643     if len(internal_control_inputs) != len(op.control_inputs):
1644       external_control_inputs = list(set(op.control_inputs)
1645                                      - set(internal_control_inputs))
1646       op._remove_all_control_inputs()
1647       op._add_control_inputs(internal_control_inputs)
1648     return internal_control_inputs, external_control_inputs
1649 
1650   # pylint: enable=protected-access
1651 
1652   def AddInnerOp(self, op):
1653     """Notifies a scope about an operator added to an inner scope."""
1654     if self._outer_context:
1655       self._outer_context.AddInnerOp(op)
1656 
1657   def GetControlPivot(self):
1658     """Returns the pivot node for this context, or None."""
1659     return None

1662     return False

1665     return False

1668     return False

1671     return self.name

1674 class CondContext(ControlFlowContext):
1675   """The context for the conditional construct."""
1676 
1677   def __init__(self,
1678                pred=None,
1679                pivot=None,
1680                branch=None,
1681                name="cond_text",
1682                context_def=None,
1683                import_scope=None):
1684     """Creates a `CondContext`.
1685 
1686     Args:
1687       pred: The `boolean` tensor for the conditional predicate.
1688       pivot: The predicate tensor in this branch.
1689       branch: 0 or 1 representing this branch.
1690       name: Name of the `CondContext` python object.
1691       context_def: Optional `ContextDef` protocol buffer to initialize the
1692         `CondContext` object from.
1693       import_scope: Optional `string`. Name scope to add. Only used when
1694         initialing from protocol buffer.
1695     """
1696     self._name = ops.get_default_graph().unique_name(name)
1697 
1698     if context_def:
1699       self._init_from_proto(context_def, import_scope=import_scope)
1700     else:
1701       # Initializes the default fields.
1702       ControlFlowContext.__init__(self)
1703       self._pred = pred  # The boolean tensor for the cond predicate
1704       self._pivot = pivot  # The predicate tensor in this branch
1705       self._branch = branch  # 0 or 1 representing this branch
1706 
1707       # Values considered to have been already seen in this context. pred is not
1708       # included in this context.
1709       self._values.add(pred.name)
1710       self._external_values[pred.name] = pred
1711       self._values.add(pivot.name)
1712       pivot.op._set_control_flow_context(self)  # pylint: disable=protected-access
1713 
1714   def _init_from_proto(self, context_def, import_scope=None):
1715     """Creates a new `CondContext` from protocol buffer.
1716 
1717     Args:
1718       context_def: `CondContextDef` protocol buffer.
1719       import_scope: Optional `string`. Name scope to add.
1720     """
1721     assert isinstance(context_def, control_flow_pb2.CondContextDef)
1722     # Create from context_def.
1723     g = ops.get_default_graph()
1724     self._name = ops.prepend_name_scope(context_def.context_name, import_scope)
1725     self._pred = g.as_graph_element(
1726         ops.prepend_name_scope(context_def.pred_name, import_scope))
1727     self._pivot = g.as_graph_element(
1728         ops.prepend_name_scope(context_def.pivot_name, import_scope))
1729     self._branch = context_def.branch
1730     super(CondContext, self).__init__(values_def=context_def.values_def,
1731                                       import_scope=import_scope)
1732 
1733   @property

1735     return self._pred
1736

1738   def pivot(self):
1739     return self._pivot

1742   def branch(self):
1743     return self._branch

1747     if self.GetWhileContext():

1749     return None
