1760   def to_proto(self, export_scope=None):
1761     """Converts a `CondContext` to a `CondContextDef` protocol buffer.
1762 
1763     Args:
1764       export_scope: Optional `string`. Name scope to remove.
1765 
1766     Returns:
1767       A `CondContextDef` protocol buffer.
1768     """
1769     if (export_scope is None or self.name.startswith(export_scope)):
1770       context_def = control_flow_pb2.CondContextDef()
1771       context_def.context_name = ops.strip_name_scope(self.name, export_scope)
1772       context_def.pred_name = ops.strip_name_scope(self._pred.name,
1773                                                    export_scope)
1774       context_def.pivot_name = ops.strip_name_scope(self._pivot.name,
1775                                                     export_scope)
1776       context_def.branch = self._branch
1777       context_def.values_def.MergeFrom(super(CondContext, self)._to_values_def(
1778           export_scope))
1779       for nested in self._nested_contexts:
1780         nested_def = context_def.nested_contexts.add()
1781         nested.to_control_flow_context_def(nested_def)
1782 
1783       return context_def
1784     else:
1785       return None
1786 
1787   @staticmethod
1788   def from_proto(context_def, import_scope=None):
1789     """Returns a `CondContext` object created from `context_def`."""
1790     ret = CondContext(context_def=context_def,
1791                       import_scope=import_scope)
1792 
1793     ret.Enter()
1794     for nested_def in context_def.nested_contexts:
1795       from_control_flow_context_def(nested_def, import_scope=import_scope)
1796     ret.Exit()
1797     return ret
1798 
1799   def to_control_flow_context_def(self, context_def, export_scope=None):
1800     context_def.cond_ctxt.CopyFrom(self.to_proto(export_scope=export_scope))
1801 
1802   def AddValue(self, val):
1803     """Add `val` to the current context and its outer context recursively."""
1804     if val.name in self._values:
1805       # Use the real value if it comes from outer context. This is needed in
1806       # particular for nested conds.
1807       result = self._external_values.get(val.name)
1808       result = val if result is None else result
1809     else:
1810       result = val
1811       self._values.add(val.name)
1812       if self._outer_context:
1813         result = self._outer_context.AddValue(val)
1814         self._values.add(result.name)
1815         self._external_values[result.name] = result
1816       with ops.control_dependencies(None):
1817         result = _SwitchRefOrTensor(result, self._pred)[self._branch]
1818         if self._outer_context:
1819           self._outer_context.AddInnerOp(result.op)
1820 
1821       result.op.graph.prevent_fetching(result.op)
1822       # pylint: disable=protected-access
1823       result.op._set_control_flow_context(self)
1824       # pylint: enable=protected-access
1825 
1826       self._values.add(result.name)
1827       self._external_values[val.name] = result
1828     return result
1829 
1830   def AddOp(self, op):
1831     self._AddOpInternal(op)
1832 
1833   def _AddOpInternal(self, op):
1834     """Add `op` to the current context."""
1835     if not op.inputs:
1836       # If we're in a while loop, remove any control inputs from outside the
1837       # loop.
1838       self._RemoveExternalControlEdges(op)
1839 
1840       if not any(util.OpInContext(input_op, self)
1841                  for input_op in op.control_inputs):
1842         # pylint: disable=protected-access
1843         op._add_control_input(self._pivot.op)
1844         # pylint: enable=protected-access
1845     else:
1846       # Make each input to 'op' available in this CondContext. If an input is
1847       # already part of this context there's nothing to do, but if it's
1848       # external, AddValue() will handle adding the appropriate Switch node and
1849       # other bookkeeping.
1850       for index in range(len(op.inputs)):
1851         x = op.inputs[index]
1852         if op.type == "Merge" and x.op.type == "NextIteration":
1853           # Edge case: if we're importing a while loop inside this CondContext,
1854           # AddValue() will not correctly handle the NextIteration inputs to
1855           # Merge node. The problem is that the NextIteration should also be
1856           # part of this context, but if we're importing it won't have been
1857           # processed and added to the context yet, so AddValue() will try to
1858           # add a Switch which results in an invalid graph. Instead, we use the
1859           # NextIteration input as-is here, and it will eventually be added to
1860           # the context via AddOp().
1861           real_x = x
1862         else:
1863           real_x = self.AddValue(x)
1864         if real_x != x:
1865           # pylint: disable=protected-access
1866           op._update_input(index, real_x)
1867           # pylint: enable=protected-access
1868       # Remove any external control dependency on this op.
1869       self._RemoveExternalControlEdges(op)
1870       # pylint: disable=protected-access
1871       if op.graph._is_function(op.type) or op.type == "SymbolicGradient":
1872         op._add_control_input(self._pivot.op)
1873       # pylint: enable=protected-access
1874 
1875     # Mark op's outputs as seen by this context and any outer contexts.
1876     output_names = [x.name for x in op.outputs]
1877     ctxt = self
1878     while ctxt is not None:
1879       # pylint: disable=protected-access
1880       ctxt._values.update(output_names)
1881       ctxt = ctxt._outer_context
1882       # pylint: enable=protected-access
1883 
1884     if self._outer_context or not util.IsLoopExit(op):
1885       op.graph.prevent_fetching(op)
1886 
1887     if self._outer_context:
1888       self._outer_context.AddInnerOp(op)
1889 
1890   def _ProcessOutputTensor(self, val):
1891     """Process an output tensor of a conditional branch."""
1892     real_val = val
1893     if val.name not in self._values:
1894       # Handle the special case of lambda: x
1895       self._values.add(val.name)
1896       if self._outer_context:
1897         real_val = self._outer_context.AddValue(val)
1898         self._values.add(real_val.name)
1899         self._external_values[real_val.name] = real_val
1900       real_val = _SwitchRefOrTensor(real_val, self._pred)[self._branch]
1901       self._external_values[val.name] = real_val
1902     else:
1903       external_val = self._external_values.get(val.name)
1904       if external_val is not None:
1905         real_val = external_val
1906     return real_val
1907 
1908   def _BuildCondTensor(self, v):
1909     if isinstance(v, ops.Operation):
1910       # Use pivot as the proxy for this op.
1911       return with_dependencies([v], self._pivot)
1912     elif isinstance(v, (ops.IndexedSlices, sparse_tensor.SparseTensor)):
1913       values = self._ProcessOutputTensor(v.values)
1914       indices = self._ProcessOutputTensor(v.indices)
1915       if isinstance(v, ops.IndexedSlices):
1916         dense_shape = v.dense_shape
1917         if dense_shape is not None:
1918           dense_shape = self._ProcessOutputTensor(dense_shape)
1919         return ops.IndexedSlices(values, indices, dense_shape)
1920       else:
1921         dense_shape = self._ProcessOutputTensor(v.dense_shape)
1922         return sparse_tensor.SparseTensor(indices, values, dense_shape)
1923     else:
1924       v = nest.map_structure(_convert_tensorarray_to_flow, v)
1925       return self._ProcessOutputTensor(ops.convert_to_tensor(v))
1926 
1927   def BuildCondBranch(self, fn):
1928     """Add the subgraph defined by fn() to the graph."""
1929     pre_summaries = ops.get_collection(ops.GraphKeys._SUMMARY_COLLECTION)  # pylint: disable=protected-access
1930     original_result = fn()
1931     post_summaries = ops.get_collection(ops.GraphKeys._SUMMARY_COLLECTION)  # pylint: disable=protected-access
1932     if len(post_summaries) > len(pre_summaries):
1933       new_summaries = post_summaries[len(pre_summaries):]
1934       summary_ref = ops.get_collection_ref(ops.GraphKeys._SUMMARY_COLLECTION)  # pylint: disable=protected-access
1935       summary_ref[:] = pre_summaries
1936       with ops.control_dependencies(new_summaries):
1937         if original_result is None:
1938           return no_op(), None
1939         else:
1940           original_result = nest.map_structure(array_ops.identity,
1941                                                original_result)
1942     if original_result is None:
1943       return None, None
1944 
1945     result = nest.map_structure(self._BuildCondTensor, original_result)
1946     if not isinstance(result, (list, _basetuple)):
1947       result = [result]
1948     return original_result, result
1949 
1950   def IsCondContext(self):
1951     return True

1954 def _UnpackIfSingleton(res):
1955   if isinstance(res, (list, _basetuple)) and len(res) == 1:
1956     return res[0]
1957   else:
1958     return res

1960 
1961 # pylint: disable=redefined-outer-name
1962 # pylint: disable=g-doc-args
1963 @tf_export("cond")
1964 @deprecation.deprecated_args(
1965     None, "fn1/fn2 are deprecated in favor of the true_fn/false_fn arguments.",
1966     "fn1", "fn2")
1967 def cond(pred,
1968          true_fn=None,
1969          false_fn=None,
1970          strict=False,
1971          name=None,
1972          fn1=None,
1973          fn2=None):
1974   """Return `true_fn()` if the predicate `pred` is true else `false_fn()`.
1975 
1976   `true_fn` and `false_fn` both return lists of output tensors. `true_fn` and
1977   `false_fn` must have the same non-zero number and type of outputs.
1978 
1979   **WARNING**: Any Tensors or Operations created outside of `true_fn` and
1980   `false_fn` will be executed regardless of which branch is selected at runtime.
1981 
1982   Although this behavior is consistent with the dataflow model of TensorFlow,
1983   it has frequently surprised users who expected a lazier semantics.
1984   Consider the following simple program:
1985 
1986   ```python
1987   z = tf.multiply(a, b)
1988   result = tf.cond(x < y, lambda: tf.add(x, z), lambda: tf.square(y))
1989   ```
1990 
1991   If `x < y`, the `tf.add` operation will be executed and `tf.square`
1992   operation will not be executed. Since `z` is needed for at least one
1993   branch of the `cond`, the `tf.multiply` operation is always executed,
1994   unconditionally.
1995 
1996   Note that `cond` calls `true_fn` and `false_fn` *exactly once* (inside the
1997   call to `cond`, and not at all during `Session.run()`). `cond`
1998   stitches together the graph fragments created during the `true_fn` and
1999   `false_fn` calls with some additional graph nodes to ensure that the right
2000   branch gets executed depending on the value of `pred`.
2001 
2002   `tf.cond` supports nested structures as implemented in
2003   `tensorflow.python.util.nest`. Both `true_fn` and `false_fn` must return the
2004   same (possibly nested) value structure of lists, tuples, and/or named tuples.
2005   Singleton lists and tuples form the only exceptions to this: when returned by
2006   `true_fn` and/or `false_fn`, they are implicitly unpacked to single values.
2007   This behavior is disabled by passing `strict=True`.
2008 
2009   Args:
2010     pred: A scalar determining whether to return the result of `true_fn` or
2011       `false_fn`.
2012     true_fn: The callable to be performed if pred is true.
2013     false_fn: The callable to be performed if pred is false.
2014     strict: A boolean that enables/disables 'strict' mode; see above.
2015     name: Optional name prefix for the returned tensors.
2016 
2017   Returns:
2018     Tensors returned by the call to either `true_fn` or `false_fn`. If the
2019     callables return a singleton list, the element is extracted from the list.
2020 
2021   Raises:
2022     TypeError: if `true_fn` or `false_fn` is not callable.
2023     ValueError: if `true_fn` and `false_fn` do not return the same number of
2024       tensors, or return tensors of different types.
2025 
2026   Example:
2027 
2028   ```python
2029   x = tf.constant(2)
2030   y = tf.constant(5)
2031   def f1(): return tf.multiply(x, 17)
2032   def f2(): return tf.add(y, 23)
2033   r = tf.cond(tf.less(x, y), f1, f2)
2034   # r is set to f1().
2035   # Operations in f2 (e.g., tf.add) are not executed.
2036   ```
2037 
2038   """
2039   if ENABLE_COND_V2 and not context.executing_eagerly():
2040     return cond_v2_impl.cond_v2(pred, true_fn, false_fn, name)
2041 
2042   # We needed to make true_fn/false_fn keyword arguments for
2043   # backwards-compatibility. This check exists so that we can convert back to
2044   # having them be positional arguments.
2045   # TODO(josh11b): Make `true_fn` and `false_fn` positional arguments after
2046   # `fn1` and `fn2` are deleted.
2047   if fn1 is not None:
2048     if true_fn is not None:
2049       raise TypeError("cond(): true_fn and fn1 may not be set simultaneously.")
2050     true_fn = fn1
2051   elif true_fn is None:
2052     raise TypeError("cond(): true_fn argument required")
2053   if fn2 is not None:
2054     if false_fn is not None:
2055       raise TypeError("cond(): false_fn and fn2 may not be set simultaneously.")
2056     false_fn = fn2
2057   elif false_fn is None:
2058     raise TypeError("cond(): false_fn argument required")
2059 
2060   if not callable(true_fn):
2061     raise TypeError("true_fn must be callable.")
2062   if not callable(false_fn):
2063     raise TypeError("false_fn must be callable.")
2064 
2065   with ops.name_scope(name, "cond", [pred]):
2066     if context.executing_eagerly():
2067       if pred:
2068         return _UnpackIfSingleton(true_fn())
2069       return _UnpackIfSingleton(false_fn())
2070 
2071     # Add the Switch to the graph.
2072     if isinstance(pred, bool):
2073       raise TypeError("pred must not be a Python bool")
2074     p_2, p_1 = switch(pred, pred)
2075     pivot_1 = array_ops.identity(p_1, name="switch_t")
2076     pivot_2 = array_ops.identity(p_2, name="switch_f")
2077     pred = array_ops.identity(pred, name="pred_id")
2078     # Disable the fetching of tensors that are only on one branch of cond.
2079     for tensor in [p_1, p_2, pivot_1, pivot_2, pred]:
2080       tensor.op.graph.prevent_fetching(tensor.op)
2081 
2082     # Build the graph for the true branch in a new context.
2083     context_t = CondContext(pred, pivot_1, branch=1)
2084     try:
2085       context_t.Enter()
2086       orig_res_t, res_t = context_t.BuildCondBranch(true_fn)
2087       if orig_res_t is None:
2088         raise ValueError("true_fn must have a return value.")
2089       context_t.ExitResult(res_t)
2090     finally:
2091       context_t.Exit()
2092 
2093     # Build the graph for the false branch in a new context.
2094     context_f = CondContext(pred, pivot_2, branch=0)
2095     try:
2096       context_f.Enter()
2097       orig_res_f, res_f = context_f.BuildCondBranch(false_fn)
2098       if orig_res_f is None:
2099         raise ValueError("false_fn must have a return value.")
2100       context_f.ExitResult(res_f)
2101     finally:
2102       context_f.Exit()
2103 
2104     if not strict:
2105       orig_res_t = _UnpackIfSingleton(orig_res_t)
2106       orig_res_f = _UnpackIfSingleton(orig_res_f)
2107 
2108     # Check that the return values of the two branches have the same structure.
2109     try:
2110       nest.assert_same_structure(orig_res_t, orig_res_f)
2111     except TypeError as e:
2112       raise TypeError(
2113           "Incompatible return types of true_fn and false_fn: {}".format(e))
2114     except ValueError as e:
2115       raise ValueError(
2116           "Incompatible return values of true_fn and false_fn: {}".format(e))
2117 
2118     # Add the final merge to the graph.
2119     if not res_t:
2120       raise ValueError("true_fn and false_fn must return at least one result.")
2121 
2122     res_t_flat = nest.flatten(res_t)
2123     res_f_flat = nest.flatten(res_f)
2124 
2125     for x, y in zip(res_t_flat, res_f_flat):
2126       assert ((isinstance(x, ops.IndexedSlices) and
2127                isinstance(y, ops.IndexedSlices)) or
2128               (isinstance(x, sparse_tensor.SparseTensor) and
2129                isinstance(y, sparse_tensor.SparseTensor)) or
2130               (isinstance(x, ops.Tensor) and isinstance(y, ops.Tensor)))
2131       val_x = x if isinstance(x, ops.Tensor) else x.values
2132       val_y = y if isinstance(y, ops.Tensor) else y.values
2133       if val_x.dtype.base_dtype != val_y.dtype.base_dtype:
2134         raise ValueError(
2135             "Outputs of true_fn and false_fn must have the same type: %s, %s" %
2136             (val_x.dtype.name, val_y.dtype.name))
2137 
2138     merges = [merge(pair)[0] for pair in zip(res_f_flat, res_t_flat)]
2139     merges = _convert_flows_to_tensorarrays(nest.flatten(orig_res_t), merges)
2140 
2141     # Only add non-nested conds to the collection. Any nested control flow will
2142     # be encapsulated in the root context.
2143     assert context_t.outer_context == context_f.outer_context
2144     if context_t.outer_context is None:
2145       ops.add_to_collection(ops.GraphKeys.COND_CONTEXT, context_t)
2146       ops.add_to_collection(ops.GraphKeys.COND_CONTEXT, context_f)
2147 
2148     merges = nest.pack_sequence_as(structure=orig_res_t, flat_sequence=merges)
2149 
2150     # Singleton lists and tuples are automatically unpacked if strict == False.
2151     if not strict:
2152       merges = _UnpackIfSingleton(merges)
2153     return merges
2154

2160 def _resource_safe_shape(t):
2161   """Returns the shape of t or the variable it points to."""
2162   if t.dtype == dtypes.resource:
2163     while t.op.inputs:
2164       t = t.op.inputs[0]
2165     return tensor_shape.TensorShape(t.op.get_attr("shape"))
2166   return array_ops.shape_internal(t, optimize=False)

2336   def to_proto(self, export_scope=None):
2337     """Converts a `WhileContext` to a `WhileContextDef` protocol buffer.
2338 
2339     Args:
2340       export_scope: Optional `string`. Name scope to remove.
2341 
2342     Returns:
2343       A `WhileContextDef` protocol buffer.
2344     """
2345     if (export_scope is None or self.name.startswith(export_scope)):
2346       context_def = control_flow_pb2.WhileContextDef()
2347       context_def.context_name = ops.strip_name_scope(self.name, export_scope)
2348       context_def.parallel_iterations = self._parallel_iterations
2349       if self._maximum_iterations is not None:
2350         context_def.maximum_iterations_name = ops.strip_name_scope(
2351             self._maximum_iterations.name, export_scope)
2352       context_def.back_prop = self._back_prop
2353       context_def.swap_memory = self._swap_memory
2354       context_def.pivot_for_pred_name = ops.strip_name_scope(
2355           self._pivot_for_pred.name, export_scope)
2356       context_def.pivot_for_body_name = ops.strip_name_scope(
2357           self._pivot_for_body.name, export_scope)
2358       context_def.pivot_name = ops.strip_name_scope(self._pivot.name,
2359                                                     export_scope)
2360       context_def.loop_exit_names.extend([
2361           ops.strip_name_scope(l.name, export_scope) for l in self._loop_exits
2362       ])
2363       context_def.loop_enter_names.extend([
2364           ops.strip_name_scope(l.name, export_scope) for l in self._loop_enters
2365       ])
2366       context_def.values_def.MergeFrom(
2367           super(WhileContext, self)._to_values_def(
2368               export_scope=export_scope))
2369       for nested in self._nested_contexts:
2370         nested_def = context_def.nested_contexts.add()
2371         nested.to_control_flow_context_def(nested_def)
2372 
2373       return context_def
2374     else:
2375       return None

2377   def to_control_flow_context_def(self, context_def, export_scope=None):
2378     context_def.while_ctxt.CopyFrom(self.to_proto(export_scope=export_scope))

2382     """Returns a `WhileContext` object created from `context_def`.
2383

2386       import_scope: Optional `string`. Name scope to add.

2407   def AddValue(self, val):
2408     """Add `val` to the current context and its outer context recursively."""
2409     result = val
2410     new_value = val.name not in self._values
2411     # Don't treat ops in this context as new values. Usually all known values
2412     # are in self._values, except when we're importing a while loop inside this
2413     # WhileContext. Since there's a cycle in this case, `val` may be part of the
2414     # imported while loop but not yet processed by this context and added to
2415     # self._values in _AddOpInternal. We only want to process external input
2416     # tensors to the while loop here.
2417     new_value &= val.op._control_flow_context is not self  # pylint: disable=protected-access
2418     if new_value:
2419       self._values.add(val.name)
2420 
2421       # If we are in a grad context and val is from its forward context,
2422       # use GetRealValue(), which adds the logic to save the history of
2423       # val in forward.
2424       grad_ctxt = ops.get_default_graph()._get_control_flow_context()
2425       if grad_ctxt:
2426         grad_ctxt = grad_ctxt.GetWhileContext()
2427         if grad_ctxt.grad_state:
2428           forward_ctxt = _GetWhileContext(val.op)
2429           if util.IsLoopExit(val.op):
2430             forward_ctxt = forward_ctxt.outer_context
2431             if forward_ctxt:
2432               forward_ctxt = forward_ctxt.GetWhileContext()
2433           if forward_ctxt == grad_ctxt.grad_state.forward_context:
2434             real_val = grad_ctxt.grad_state.GetRealValue(val)
2435             self._external_values[val.name] = real_val
2436             return real_val
2437 
2438       if self._outer_context is not None:
2439         result = self._outer_context.AddValue(val)
2440       # Create an Enter to make `result` known to this loop context.
2441       with ops.control_dependencies(None):
2442         enter = _Enter(
2443             result,
2444             self._name,
2445             is_constant=True,
2446             parallel_iterations=self._parallel_iterations)
2447         enter.graph.prevent_feeding(enter)
2448         if self._outer_context:
2449           self._outer_context.AddInnerOp(enter.op)
2450       # Fix the control inputs and control flow context of these enter ops.
2451       self._FixControlInputsAndContext([enter])
2452 
2453       # Add `enter` in this context.
2454       self._values.add(enter.name)
2455       self._external_values[val.name] = enter
2456       result = enter
2457     else:
2458       actual_val = self._external_values.get(val.name)
2459       if actual_val is not None:
2460         result = actual_val
2461     return result
2462 
2463   def AddOp(self, op):
2464     """Add `op` to the current context."""
2465     # For a reduction op, if op is in a grad context and its input is from
2466     # its forward context, moving op to the forward context means we would
2467     # store the tensor after the reduction as opposed to the tensor before
2468     # reduction, and therefore could significantly reduce memory consumption.
2469     # For now, we do this only for a few ops.
2470     if op.type in {"Shape", "Size", "Rank"}:
2471       grad_ctxt = ops.get_default_graph()._get_control_flow_context()
2472       if grad_ctxt:
2473         grad_ctxt = grad_ctxt.GetWhileContext()
2474         if grad_ctxt.grad_state:
2475           op_input_forward_ctxt = _GetWhileContext(op.inputs[0].op)
2476           if op_input_forward_ctxt == grad_ctxt.grad_state.forward_context:
2477             op_input_ctxt = op.inputs[0].op._get_control_flow_context()
2478             op._set_control_flow_context(op_input_ctxt)
2479             op_input_ctxt._AddOpInternal(op)
2480             return
2481     self._AddOpInternal(op)
2482 
2483   def _AddOpInternal(self, op):
2484     """Add `op` to the current context.
2485 
2486     We move any external control dependencies of the op to the loop pivot, to
2487     ensure they get executed.
2488     """
2489     if not op.inputs:
2490       # Remove any external control dependency on this op
2491       control_inputs, external_inputs = self._RemoveExternalControlEdges(op)
2492       # Add a control edge from the control pivot to this op.
2493       if not control_inputs:
2494         # pylint: disable=protected-access
2495         op._add_control_input(self.GetControlPivot().op)
2496         # pylint: enable=protected-access
2497       for x in op.outputs:
2498         self._values.add(x.name)
2499     else:
2500       for index in range(len(op.inputs)):
2501         x = op.inputs[index]
2502         real_x = self.AddValue(x)
2503         if real_x != x:
2504           op._update_input(index, real_x)  # pylint: disable=protected-access
2505       # Remove any external control dependency on this op.
2506       _, external_inputs = self._RemoveExternalControlEdges(op)
2507       # Add a control dependency to prevent loop invariants from
2508       # enabling ops that should not be executed.
2509       self._MaybeAddControlDependency(op)
2510       for x in op.outputs:
2511         self._values.add(x.name)
2512     if external_inputs:
2513       # Use an identity to pull control inputs as data inputs. Note that we
2514       # ignore ops which don't have outputs. TODO(apassos): fix that
2515       with ops.control_dependencies(None):
2516         self.Enter()
2517         external_inputs = [array_ops.identity(x.outputs[0]).op
2518                            for x in external_inputs if x.outputs]
2519         self.Exit()
2520       op._add_control_inputs(external_inputs)  # pylint: disable=protected-access
2521     if self._outer_context or not util.IsLoopExit(op):
2522       op.graph.prevent_fetching(op)
2523       for x in op.outputs:
2524         op.graph.prevent_feeding(x)
2525 
2526     if self._outer_context:
2527       self._outer_context.AddInnerOp(op)
2528 
2529   def _MaybeAddControlDependency(self, op):
2530     """Add a control input to the op if it only depends on loop invariants."""
2531 
2532     def _IsOpFree(op):
2533       """Determines if `op` needs a control dependency."""
2534       if op.control_inputs:
2535         return False
2536       # pylint: disable=protected-access
2537       if op.graph._is_function(op.type) or op.type == "SymbolicGradient":
2538         return True
2539       # pylint: enable=protected-access
2540       for x in op.inputs:
2541         if not util.IsLoopConstantEnter(x.op):
2542           return False
2543       return True
2544 
2545     if _IsOpFree(op):
2546       # pylint: disable=protected-access
2547       op._add_control_input(self.GetControlPivot().op)
2548       # pylint: enable=protected-access
2549 
2550   def AddForwardLoopCounter(self, outer_grad_state):
2551     """Adds a loop that counts the number of iterations.
2552 
2553     This is added to the forward loop at the time when we start to
2554     create the loop for backprop gradient computation. Called in
2555     the outer context of this forward context.
2556 
2557     The pseudocode is:
2558       `n = 0; while (_pivot) { n++; }`
2559 
2560     Note that a control dependency is added to `n` to ensure the correct
2561     execution order of stack push ops.
2562 
2563     Args:
2564       outer_grad_state: The outer grad state. None if not nested.
2565 
2566     Returns:
2567       The number of iterations taken by the forward loop and the loop index.
2568     """
2569     n = constant_op.constant(0, name="f_count")
2570     if outer_grad_state is not None:
2571       # Force the stack pushes of i-th execution of an inner loop to be ordered
2572       # before the pushes of (i+1)-th execution of the same inner loop.
2573       outer_add_op = outer_grad_state.forward_index.op.inputs[0].op
2574       n.op._add_control_input(outer_add_op)  # pylint: disable=protected-access
2575 
2576     self.Enter()
2577     self.AddName(n.name)
2578     enter_n = _Enter(
2579         n,
2580         self._name,
2581         is_constant=False,
2582         parallel_iterations=self._parallel_iterations,
2583         name="f_count")
2584     self.loop_enters.append(enter_n)
2585 
2586     merge_n = merge([enter_n, enter_n])[0]
2587     switch_n = switch(merge_n, self._pivot)
2588 
2589     index = math_ops.add(switch_n[1], 1)
2590     next_n = _NextIteration(index)
2591     merge_n.op._update_input(1, next_n)
2592 
2593     total_iterations = exit(switch_n[0], name="f_count")
2594     self.loop_exits.append(total_iterations)
2595     self.ExitResult([total_iterations])
2596     self.Exit()
2597     return total_iterations, next_n
2598 
2599   def AddBackpropLoopCounter(self, count, outer_grad_state):
2600     """Add the backprop loop that controls the iterations.
2601 
2602     This is added to the backprop loop. It is used to control the loop
2603     termination of the backprop loop. Called in the outer context of
2604     this grad context.
2605 
2606     The pseudocode is:
2607       `n = count; while (n >= 1) { n--; }`
2608 
2609     Note that a control dependency is added to `final_zero` to ensure the
2610     correct execution order of stack pop ops.
2611 
2612     Args:
2613       count: The number of iterations for backprop.
2614       outer_grad_state: The outer grad state. None if not nested.
2615 
2616     Returns:
2617       The loop index.
2618     """
2619     in_separate_functions = count.graph is not ops.get_default_graph()
2620     if in_separate_functions:
2621       # Brings the count into this graph
2622       count = array_ops.identity(count)
2623     else:
2624       # TODO(apassos) XLA expects this constant to be created outside the loop,
2625       # so doing that for now.
2626       one = constant_op.constant(1, name="b_count")
2627 
2628     self.Enter()
2629     self.AddName(count.name)
2630     enter_count = _Enter(
2631         count,
2632         self._name,
2633         is_constant=False,
2634         parallel_iterations=self._parallel_iterations,
2635         name="b_count")
2636     self.loop_enters.append(enter_count)
2637 
2638     merge_count = merge([enter_count, enter_count])[0]
2639     self._pivot_for_pred = merge_count
2640 
2641     if in_separate_functions:
2642       one = constant_op.constant(1, name="b_count")
2643     pred = math_ops.greater_equal(merge_count, one)
2644     self._pivot = loop_cond(pred, name="b_count")
2645     switch_count = switch(merge_count, self._pivot)
2646 
2647     index = math_ops.subtract(switch_count[1], one)
2648     self._pivot_for_body = index
2649     next_count = _NextIteration(index)
2650     merge_count.op._update_input(1, next_count)
2651 
2652     final_zero = exit(switch_count[0], name="b_count")
2653     self.loop_exits.append(final_zero)
2654     if outer_grad_state is not None:
2655       # Force the stack pops of i-th execution of an inner loop to be ordered
2656       # before the pops of (i+1)-th execution of the same inner loop.
2657       # pylint: disable=protected-access
2658       outer_grad_state.grad_sync._add_control_input(final_zero.op)
2659       # pylint: enable=protected-access
2660 
2661     self.ExitResult([final_zero])
2662     self.Exit()
2663     return next_count
2664 
2665   def AddBackpropAccumulator(self, op, grad):
2666     """Add an accumulation loop for every loop invariant.
2667 
2668     This is added to the backprop loop. It is used to accumulate partial
2669     gradients within each loop iteration. Called when in the gradient while
2670     context.
2671 
2672     The pseudocode is:
2673       ```
2674       acc = 0.0;
2675       while (_pivot) {
2676         acc += grad;
2677       }
2678       ```
2679 
2680     Args:
2681       op: The Enter op for a loop invariant.
2682       grad: The partial gradient of an iteration for a loop invariant.
2683 
2684     Returns:
2685       The gradient for a loop invariant.
2686     """
2687     self.Exit()
2688     # Create a zeros tensor with the right shape for acc. If we don't
2689     # know the full shape statically, we will have to get the shape
2690     # dynamically from the forward inference. Getting the shape right
2691     # for the zeros is only needed for the base case when the loop exits
2692     # without running any iterations.
2693     shape = grad.get_shape()
2694     if shape.is_fully_defined():
2695       if self.outer_context:
2696         self.outer_context.Enter()
2697       acc = constant_op.constant(0, grad.dtype, shape=shape, name="b_acc")
2698       if self.outer_context:
2699         self.outer_context.Exit()
2700     else:
2701       value = op.inputs[0]
2702       if (isinstance(self.outer_context, WhileContext) and
2703           self.outer_context.grad_state is not None):
2704         # We are in a nested while loop.
2705         forward_ctxt = self.grad_state.forward_context
2706         forward_ctxt.outer_context.Enter()
2707         zeros_shape = array_ops.shape_internal(value, optimize=False)
2708         forward_ctxt.outer_context.Exit()
2709         outer_grad_state = self.grad_state.outer_grad_state
2710         history_zeros_shape = outer_grad_state.AddForwardAccumulator(
2711             zeros_shape)
2712         self.outer_context.Enter()
2713         real_shape = outer_grad_state.AddBackpropAccumulatedValue(
2714             history_zeros_shape, zeros_shape)
2715         acc = array_ops.zeros(real_shape, grad.dtype)
2716         self.outer_context.Exit()
2717       else:
2718         if self.outer_context:
2719           self.outer_context.Enter()
2720         zeros_shape = array_ops.shape_internal(value, optimize=False)
2721         acc = array_ops.zeros(zeros_shape, grad.dtype)
2722         if self.outer_context:
2723           self.outer_context.Exit()
2724 
2725     self.Enter()
2726     self.AddName(acc.name)
2727     enter_acc = _Enter(
2728         acc,
2729         self._name,
2730         is_constant=False,
2731         parallel_iterations=self._parallel_iterations,
2732         name="b_acc")
2733     self.loop_enters.append(enter_acc)
2734 
2735     merge_acc = merge([enter_acc, enter_acc], name="b_acc")[0]
2736     switch_acc_false, switch_acc_true = switch(merge_acc, self._pivot)
2737 
2738     add_acc = math_ops.add(switch_acc_true, grad)
2739     next_acc = _NextIteration(add_acc)
2740     merge_acc.op._update_input(1, next_acc)  # pylint: disable=protected-access
2741 
2742     result_acc = exit(switch_acc_false, name="b_acc")
2743     self.loop_exits.append(result_acc)
2744     self.ExitResult([result_acc])
2745     return result_acc

2747   def AddBackpropIndexedSlicesAccumulator(self, op, grad):
2748     """This is used for accumulating gradients that are IndexedSlices.
2749 
2750     This is essentially the equivalent of AddBackpropAccumulator but optimized
2751     for things like updating embeddings from within a while loop.
2752 
2753     Args:
2754       op: The Enter op for a loop invariant.
2755       grad: The partial gradients represented as an IndexedSlices.
2756 
2757     Returns:
2758       The accumulated IndexedSlices gradient of the loop invariant.
2759     """
2760     values = grad.values
2761     indices = grad.indices
2762     dense_shape = grad.dense_shape
2763 
2764     self.Exit()
2765     if self.outer_context:
2766       self.outer_context.Enter()
2767     if values.get_shape().is_fully_defined():
2768       values_shape = tensor_shape.TensorShape(
2769           [tensor_shape.Dimension(1)] + values.get_shape().dims[1:])
2770       if self.outer_context:
2771         self.outer_context.Enter()
2772       values_acc = constant_op.constant(
2773           0, values.dtype, shape=values_shape, name="b_acc")
2774       if self.outer_context:
2775         self.outer_context.Exit()
2776     else:
2777       values_shape = _resource_safe_shape(op.inputs[0])[1:]
2778       values_shape = array_ops.concat([[1], values_shape], 0)
2779       values_acc = array_ops.zeros(values_shape, dtype=values.dtype)
2780     indices_acc = constant_op.constant([0], indices.dtype)
2781     shape_acc = None
2782     if dense_shape is not None:
2783       if dense_shape.get_shape().is_fully_defined():
2784         if self.outer_context:
2785           self.outer_context.Enter()
2786         shape_acc = constant_op.constant(
2787             0, dense_shape.dtype, shape=dense_shape.get_shape())
2788         if self.outer_context:
2789           self.outer_context.Exit()
2790       else:
2791         shape_acc = array_ops.zeros_like(
2792             array_ops.shape_internal(op.inputs[0], optimize=False,
2793                                      out_type=dense_shape.dtype),
2794             optimize=False)
2795 
2796     if self.outer_context:
2797       self.outer_context.Exit()
2798 
2799     self.Enter()
2800     self.AddName(values_acc.name)
2801     self.AddName(indices_acc.name)
2802     init_acc = [indices_acc, values_acc]
2803     if shape_acc is not None:
2804       self.AddName(shape_acc.name)
2805       init_acc.append(shape_acc)
2806 
2807     # Set use_input_shape=False since the accumulator tensors will grow in
2808     # size. If use_input_shape=True, the _update_input call below will result in
2809     # incompatible shapes.
2810     enter_acc = [
2811         _Enter(
2812             x,
2813             self._name,
2814             is_constant=False,
2815             parallel_iterations=self._parallel_iterations,
2816             use_input_shape=False,
2817             name="b_acc") for x in init_acc
2818     ]
2819     # Manually set appropriate partial shapes.
2820     enter_acc[0].set_shape([None])
2821     if values_acc.shape.dims is not None:
2822       enter_acc[1].set_shape([None] + values_acc.shape.as_list()[1:])
2823     self.loop_enters.extend(enter_acc)
2824 
2825     merge_acc = [merge([x, x], name="b_acc")[0] for x in enter_acc]
2826     switch_acc = [switch(x, self._pivot) for x in merge_acc]
2827 
2828     # The actual accumulation.
2829     acc_indexed_slices = [
2830         array_ops.concat([xa[1], xv], 0)
2831         for xa, xv in zip(switch_acc[:2], [indices, values])
2832     ]
2833     if shape_acc is not None:
2834       # For the shape we just keep the maximum
2835       acc_indexed_slices.append(math_ops.maximum(dense_shape, switch_acc[2][1]))
2836 
2837     next_acc = [_NextIteration(x) for x in acc_indexed_slices]
2838     for xm, xn in zip(merge_acc, next_acc):
2839       xm.op._update_input(1, xn)  # pylint: disable=protected-access
2840 
2841     exit_acc = [exit(x[0], name="b_acc") for x in switch_acc]
2842     self.loop_exits.extend(exit_acc)
2843 
2844     self.ExitResult(exit_acc)
2845     return ops.IndexedSlices(
2846         indices=exit_acc[0],
2847         values=exit_acc[1],
2848         dense_shape=exit_acc[2] if shape_acc is not None else None)

2850   def _InitializeValues(self, values):
2851     """Makes the values known to this context."""
2852     self._values = set()
2853     for x in values:
2854       if isinstance(x, ops.Tensor):
2855         self._values.add(x.name)
2856       else:
2857         self._values.add(x.values.name)
2858         self._values.add(x.indices.name)
2859         if isinstance(x, ops.IndexedSlices):
2860           dense_shape = x.dense_shape
2861         elif isinstance(x, sparse_tensor.SparseTensor):

2865         if dense_shape is not None:

2868   def _BuildLoop(self, pred, body, original_loop_vars, loop_vars,
2869                  shape_invariants):
2870     """Core: Add the loop termination condition and body to the graph."""
2871     flat_loop_vars = nest.flatten(original_loop_vars)
2872 
2873     # Let the context know the loop variables so the loop variables
2874     # would be added in the outer contexts properly.
2875     self._InitializeValues(loop_vars)
2876     real_vars = loop_vars
2877     if self._outer_context:
2878       real_vars = [self._outer_context.AddValue(x) for x in loop_vars]
2879     with ops.control_dependencies(None):
2880       enter_vars = [
2881           _Enter(
2882               x,
2883               self._name,
2884               is_constant=False,
2885               parallel_iterations=self._parallel_iterations,
2886               use_input_shape=(shape_invariants is None)) for x in real_vars
2887       ]
2888       for x in enter_vars:
2889         x.graph.prevent_feeding(x)
2890         if self._outer_context:
2891           self._outer_context.AddInnerOp(x.op)
2892 
2893     # Finds the closest enclosing non-None control pivot.
2894     outer_context = self._outer_context
2895     control_pivot = None
2896     while outer_context is not None and control_pivot is None:
2897       control_pivot = outer_context.GetControlPivot()
2898       # pylint: disable=protected-access
2899       outer_context = outer_context._outer_context
2900       # pylint: enable=protected-access
2901 
2902     if control_pivot is not None:
2903       for var in enter_vars:
2904         if util.IsLoopConstantEnter(var.op.inputs[0].op):
2905           # pylint: disable=protected-access
2906           var.op._add_control_input(control_pivot.op)
2907           # pylint: enable=protected-access
2908     _SetShapeInvariants(real_vars, enter_vars, shape_invariants)
2909 
2910     # Fix the control inputs and control flow context of these enter ops.
2911     self._FixControlInputsAndContext(enter_vars)
2912     self._InitializeValues(enter_vars)
2913     self._loop_enters = enter_vars
2914 
2915     merge_vars = [merge([x, x])[0] for x in enter_vars]
2916     self._pivot_for_pred = merge_vars[0]
2917 
2918     # Build the graph for pred.
2919     merge_vars_with_tensor_arrays = (
2920         _convert_flows_to_tensorarrays(flat_loop_vars, merge_vars))
2921     packed_vars = nest.pack_sequence_as(
2922         structure=original_loop_vars,
2923         flat_sequence=merge_vars_with_tensor_arrays)
2924     c = ops.convert_to_tensor(pred(*packed_vars))
2925     self._pivot = loop_cond(c, name="LoopCond")
2926     switch_vars = [_SwitchRefOrTensor(x, self._pivot) for x in merge_vars]
2927 
2928     # Build the graph for body.
2929     vars_for_body = [_Identity(x[1]) for x in switch_vars]
2930     self._pivot_for_body = vars_for_body[0]
2931     # Convert TensorArray flow variables inside the context back into
2932     # their associated TensorArrays for calling the body.
2933     vars_for_body_with_tensor_arrays = (
2934         _convert_flows_to_tensorarrays(flat_loop_vars, vars_for_body))
2935     packed_vars_for_body = nest.pack_sequence_as(
2936         structure=original_loop_vars,
2937         flat_sequence=vars_for_body_with_tensor_arrays)
2938     pre_summaries = ops.get_collection(ops.GraphKeys._SUMMARY_COLLECTION)  # pylint: disable=protected-access
2939     body_result = body(*packed_vars_for_body)
2940     post_summaries = ops.get_collection(ops.GraphKeys._SUMMARY_COLLECTION)  # pylint: disable=protected-access
2941     if not nest.is_sequence(body_result):
2942       body_result = [body_result]
2943     if len(post_summaries) > len(pre_summaries):
2944       new_summaries = post_summaries[len(pre_summaries):]
2945       summary_ref = ops.get_collection_ref(ops.GraphKeys._SUMMARY_COLLECTION)  # pylint: disable=protected-access
2946       summary_ref[:] = pre_summaries
2947       with ops.control_dependencies(new_summaries):
2948 
2949         def map_fn(x):
2950           # TODO(apassos) figure out how to trigger with tensor arrays as well
2951           if isinstance(x, tensor_array_ops.TensorArray):
2952             return x
2953           return array_ops.identity(x)
2954 
2955         body_result = nest.map_structure(map_fn, body_result)
2956 
2957     # Compare the structure types of input and output of body.
2958     # For backwards compatibility, the first layer is forced to a list
2959     # during this comparison, because inputs are typically lists and
2960     # outputs of the body are typically tuples.
2961     nest.assert_same_structure(list(packed_vars_for_body), list(body_result))
2962 
2963     # Store body_result to keep track of TensorArrays returned by body
2964     original_body_result = body_result
2965     # Convert TensorArrays returned by body into their flow variables
2966     result = nest.map_structure(_convert_tensorarray_to_flow,
2967                                 nest.flatten(body_result))
2968     result = ops.convert_n_to_tensor_or_indexed_slices(result)
2969 
2970     # Add NextIteration and the back edges to complete the loop.
2971     if len(merge_vars) != len(result):
2972       raise ValueError("Number of inputs and outputs of body must match "
2973                        "loop_vars: %d, %d" % (len(merge_vars), len(result)))
2974     next_vars = []
2975     for m, v in zip(merge_vars, result):
2976       next_vars.append(_AddNextAndBackEdge(m, v))
2977 
2978     # Add the exit ops.
2979     exit_vars = [exit(x[0]) for x in switch_vars]
2980     self._loop_exits = exit_vars
2981 
2982     # Exit the loop.
2983     self.ExitResult(exit_vars)
2984 
2985     return original_body_result, exit_vars
2986 
2987   def BuildLoop(self, pred, body, loop_vars, shape_invariants,
2988                 return_same_structure):
2989     """Add the loop termination condition and body to the graph."""
2990 
2991     # Keep original_loop_vars to identify which are TensorArrays
2992     original_loop_vars = loop_vars
2993     # Convert TensorArrays to their flow variables
2994     loop_vars = nest.map_structure(_convert_tensorarray_to_flow,
2995                                    nest.flatten(loop_vars))
2996     loop_vars = ops.convert_n_to_tensor_or_indexed_slices(loop_vars)
2997     try:
2998       self.Enter()
2999       # _BuildLoop calls _update_input in several places. _mutation_lock()
3000       # ensures a Session.run call cannot occur between creating and mutating
3001       # new ops.
3002       with ops.get_default_graph()._mutation_lock():  # pylint: disable=protected-access
3003         original_body_result, exit_vars = self._BuildLoop(
3004             pred, body, original_loop_vars, loop_vars, shape_invariants)
3005     finally:
3006       self.Exit()
3007 
3008     flat_result = nest.flatten(original_body_result)
3009     # Convert TensorArray flow variables outside the context back into
3010     # their associated TensorArrays for returning to caller.
3011     exit_vars_with_tensor_arrays = (
3012         _convert_flows_to_tensorarrays(flat_result, exit_vars))
3013     packed_exit_vars = nest.pack_sequence_as(
3014         structure=original_body_result,
3015         flat_sequence=exit_vars_with_tensor_arrays)
3016 
3017     if return_same_structure:
3018       return packed_exit_vars
3019     else:
3020       return packed_exit_vars[0] if len(exit_vars) == 1 else packed_exit_vars

3022   def _FixControlInputsAndContext(self, enters):
3023     graph = ops.get_default_graph()
3024     # pylint: disable=protected-access
3025     for e in enters:
3026       if isinstance(e, ops.Tensor):
3027         xs = [e]
3028       else:
3029         if not isinstance(e, (ops.IndexedSlices, sparse_tensor.SparseTensor)):
3030           raise TypeError("Type %s not supported" % type(e))
3031         xs = [e.values, e.indices]
3032         shape = e.dense_shape
3033         if shape is not None:
3034           xs.append(shape)
3035       for x in xs:
3036         inp_op = x.op.inputs[0].op
3037         control_inputs = graph._control_dependencies_for_inputs([inp_op])
3038         outer_control_inputs = [
3039             op for op in control_inputs if self._IsInOuterContext(op)
3040         ]
3041         x.op._set_control_flow_context(self)
3042         x.op._add_control_inputs(outer_control_inputs)
3043         graph._record_op_seen_by_control_dependencies(x.op)

3050 # pylint: disable=redefined-outer-name
3051 @tf_export("while_loop")
3052 def while_loop(cond,
3053                body,
3054                loop_vars,
3055                shape_invariants=None,
3056                parallel_iterations=10,
3057                back_prop=True,
3058                swap_memory=False,
3059                name=None,
3060                maximum_iterations=None,
3061                return_same_structure=False):
3062   """Repeat `body` while the condition `cond` is true.
3063 
3064   `cond` is a callable returning a boolean scalar tensor. `body` is a callable
3065   returning a (possibly nested) tuple, namedtuple or list of tensors of the same
3066   arity (length and structure) and types as `loop_vars`. `loop_vars` is a
3067   (possibly nested) tuple, namedtuple or list of tensors that is passed to both
3068   `cond` and `body`. `cond` and `body` both take as many arguments as there are
3069   `loop_vars`.
3070 
3071   In addition to regular Tensors or IndexedSlices, the body may accept and
3072   return TensorArray objects.  The flows of the TensorArray objects will
3073   be appropriately forwarded between loops and during gradient calculations.
3074 
3075   Note that `while_loop` calls `cond` and `body` *exactly once* (inside the
3076   call to `while_loop`, and not at all during `Session.run()`). `while_loop`
3077   stitches together the graph fragments created during the `cond` and `body`
3078   calls with some additional graph nodes to create the graph flow that
3079   repeats `body` until `cond` returns false.
3080 
3081   For correctness, `tf.while_loop()` strictly enforces shape invariants for
3082   the loop variables. A shape invariant is a (possibly partial) shape that
3083   is unchanged across the iterations of the loop. An error will be raised
3084   if the shape of a loop variable after an iteration is determined to be more
3085   general than or incompatible with its shape invariant. For example, a shape
3086   of [11, None] is more general than a shape of [11, 17], and [11, 21] is not
3087   compatible with [11, 17]. By default (if the argument `shape_invariants` is
3088   not specified), it is assumed that the initial shape of each tensor in
3089   `loop_vars` is the same in every iteration. The `shape_invariants` argument
3090   allows the caller to specify a less specific shape invariant for each loop
3091   variable, which is needed if the shape varies between iterations. The
3092   `tf.Tensor.set_shape`
3093   function may also be used in the `body` function to indicate that
3094   the output loop variable has a particular shape. The shape invariant for
3095   SparseTensor and IndexedSlices are treated specially as follows:
3096 
3097   a) If a loop variable is a SparseTensor, the shape invariant must be
3098   TensorShape([r]) where r is the rank of the dense tensor represented
3099   by the sparse tensor. It means the shapes of the three tensors of the
3100   SparseTensor are ([None], [None, r], [r]). NOTE: The shape invariant here
3101   is the shape of the SparseTensor.dense_shape property. It must be the shape of
3102   a vector.
3103 
3104   b) If a loop variable is an IndexedSlices, the shape invariant must be
3105   a shape invariant of the values tensor of the IndexedSlices. It means
3106   the shapes of the three tensors of the IndexedSlices are (shape, [shape[0]],
3107   [shape.ndims]).
3108 
3109   `while_loop` implements non-strict semantics, enabling multiple iterations
3110   to run in parallel. The maximum number of parallel iterations can be
3111   controlled by `parallel_iterations`, which gives users some control over
3112   memory consumption and execution order. For correct programs, `while_loop`
3113   should return the same result for any parallel_iterations > 0.
3114 
3115   For training, TensorFlow stores the tensors that are produced in the
3116   forward inference and are needed in back propagation. These tensors are a
3117   main source of memory consumption and often cause OOM errors when training
3118   on GPUs. When the flag swap_memory is true, we swap out these tensors from
3119   GPU to CPU. This for example allows us to train RNN models with very long
3120   sequences and large batches.
3121 
3122   Args:
3123     cond: A callable that represents the termination condition of the loop.
3124     body: A callable that represents the loop body.
3125     loop_vars: A (possibly nested) tuple, namedtuple or list of numpy array,
3126       `Tensor`, and `TensorArray` objects.
3127     shape_invariants: The shape invariants for the loop variables.
3128     parallel_iterations: The number of iterations allowed to run in parallel.
3129       It must be a positive integer.
3130     back_prop: Whether backprop is enabled for this while loop.
3131     swap_memory: Whether GPU-CPU memory swap is enabled for this loop.
3132     name: Optional name prefix for the returned tensors.
3133     maximum_iterations: Optional maximum number of iterations of the while loop
3134       to run.  If provided, the `cond` output is AND-ed with an additional
3135       condition ensuring the number of iterations executed is no greater than
3136       `maximum_iterations`.
3137     return_same_structure: If True, output has same structure as `loop_vars`. If
3138       eager execution is enabled, this is ignored (and always treated as True).
3139 
3140   Returns:
3141     The output tensors for the loop variables after the loop.
3142      If `return_same_structure` is True, the return value has the same
3143      structure as `loop_vars`.
3144      If `return_same_structure` is False, the return value is a Tensor,
3145      TensorArray or IndexedSlice if the length of `loop_vars` is 1, or a list
3146      otherwise.
3147 
3148   Raises:
3149     TypeError: if `cond` or `body` is not callable.
3150     ValueError: if `loop_vars` is empty.
3151 
3152   Example:
3153 
3154   ```python
3155   i = tf.constant(0)
3156   c = lambda i: tf.less(i, 10)
3157   b = lambda i: tf.add(i, 1)
3158   r = tf.while_loop(c, b, [i])
3159   ```
3160 
3161   Example with nesting and a namedtuple:
3162 
3163   ```python
3164   import collections
3165   Pair = collections.namedtuple('Pair', 'j, k')
3166   ijk_0 = (tf.constant(0), Pair(tf.constant(1), tf.constant(2)))
3167   c = lambda i, p: i < 10
3168   b = lambda i, p: (i + 1, Pair((p.j + p.k), (p.j - p.k)))
3169   ijk_final = tf.while_loop(c, b, ijk_0)
3170   ```
3171 
3172   Example using shape_invariants:
3173 
3174   ```python
3175   i0 = tf.constant(0)
3176   m0 = tf.ones([2, 2])
3177   c = lambda i, m: i < 10
3178   b = lambda i, m: [i+1, tf.concat([m, m], axis=0)]
3179   tf.while_loop(
3180       c, b, loop_vars=[i0, m0],
3181       shape_invariants=[i0.get_shape(), tf.TensorShape([None, 2])])
3182   ```
3183 
3184   Example which demonstrates non-strict semantics: In the following
3185   example, the final value of the counter `i` does not depend on `x`. So
3186   the `while_loop` can increment the counter parallel to updates of `x`.
3187   However, because the loop counter at one loop iteration depends
3188   on the value at the previous iteration, the loop counter itself cannot
3189   be incremented in parallel. Hence if we just want the final value of the
3190   counter (which we print on the line `print(sess.run(i))`), then
3191   `x` will never be incremented, but the counter will be updated on a
3192   single thread. Conversely, if we want the value of the output (which we
3193   print on the line `print(sess.run(out).shape)`), then the counter may be
3194   incremented on its own thread, while `x` can be incremented in
3195   parallel on a separate thread. In the extreme case, it is conceivable
3196   that the thread incrementing the counter runs until completion before
3197   `x` is incremented even a single time. The only thing that can never
3198   happen is that the thread updating `x` can never get ahead of the
3199   counter thread because the thread incrementing `x` depends on the value
3200   of the counter.
3201 
3202   ```python
3203   import tensorflow as tf
3204 
3205   n = 10000
3206   x = tf.constant(list(range(n)))
3207   c = lambda i, x: i < n
3208   b = lambda i, x: (tf.Print(i + 1, [i]), tf.Print(x + 1, [i], "x:"))
3209   i, out = tf.while_loop(c, b, (0, x))
3210   with tf.Session() as sess:
3211       print(sess.run(i))  # prints [0] ... [9999]
3212 
3213       # The following line may increment the counter and x in parallel.
3214       # The counter thread may get ahead of the other thread, but not the
3215       # other way around. So you may see things like
3216       # [9996] x:[9987]
3217       # meaning that the counter thread is on iteration 9996,
3218       # while the other thread is on iteration 9987
3219       print(sess.run(out).shape)
3220   ```
3221 
3222   """
3223   if ENABLE_WHILE_V2 and not context.executing_eagerly():
3224     if not _while_v2:
3225       raise ValueError("The while_v2 module is not set. Did you forget to "
3226                        "import tensorflow.python.ops."
3227                        "while_v2?")
3228     return _while_v2.while_loop(cond, body, loop_vars, name)
3229 
3230   with ops.name_scope(name, "while", loop_vars):
3231     if not loop_vars:
3232       raise ValueError("No loop variables provided")
3233     if not callable(cond):
3234       raise TypeError("cond must be callable.")
3235     if not callable(body):
3236       raise TypeError("body must be callable.")
3237     if parallel_iterations < 1:
3238       raise TypeError("parallel_iterations must be a positive integer.")
3239 
3240     if maximum_iterations is not None:
3241       maximum_iterations = ops.convert_to_tensor(
3242           maximum_iterations, name="maximum_iterations")
3243       if maximum_iterations.shape.ndims != 0:
3244         raise ValueError("maximum_iterations must be a scalar, saw shape: %s" %
3245                          maximum_iterations.shape)
3246 
3247       counter = constant_op.constant(
3248           0, dtype=maximum_iterations.dtype, name="iteration_counter")
3249       orig_cond = cond
3250       orig_body = body
3251       if len(loop_vars) == 1:
3252         loop_vars = (counter, loop_vars[0])
3253         cond = lambda i, lv: (  # pylint: disable=g-long-lambda
3254             math_ops.logical_and(i < maximum_iterations, orig_cond(lv)))
3255         body = lambda i, lv: (i + 1, orig_body(lv))
3256       else:
3257         loop_vars = (counter, loop_vars)
3258         cond = lambda i, lv: (  # pylint: disable=g-long-lambda
3259             math_ops.logical_and(i < maximum_iterations, orig_cond(*lv)))
3260         body = lambda i, lv: (i + 1, orig_body(*lv))
3261 
3262     if context.executing_eagerly():
3263       try_to_pack = len(loop_vars) == 1
3264       packed = False  # whether the body result was packed into a 1-item tuple
3265 
3266       while cond(*loop_vars):
3267         loop_vars = body(*loop_vars)
3268         if try_to_pack and not isinstance(loop_vars, (list, _basetuple)):
3269           packed = True
3270           loop_vars = (loop_vars,)
3271       if maximum_iterations is not None:
3272         return loop_vars[1]
3273       else:
3274         return loop_vars[0] if packed else loop_vars
3275 
3276     if shape_invariants is not None:
3277       if maximum_iterations is not None:
3278         shape_invariants = (tensor_shape.TensorShape([]), shape_invariants)
3279       nest.assert_same_structure(loop_vars, shape_invariants)
3280 
3281     loop_context = WhileContext(
3282         maximum_iterations=maximum_iterations,
3283         parallel_iterations=parallel_iterations,
3284         back_prop=back_prop,
3285         swap_memory=swap_memory)
3286     # Only add non-nested loops to the collection. Any nested control flow will
3287     # be encapsulated in the root context.
3288     if loop_context.outer_context is None:
3289       ops.add_to_collection(ops.GraphKeys.WHILE_CONTEXT, loop_context)
3290     result = loop_context.BuildLoop(cond, body, loop_vars, shape_invariants,
3291                                     return_same_structure)
3292     if maximum_iterations is not None:
3293       return result[1]
3294     else:
3295       return result

3301 def _AsTensorList(x, p):
3302   """Return x as a list of Tensors or IndexedSlices.
3303 
3304   For entries of `x` that are Operations, this returns an Identity of `p`
3305   with a dependency on the operation.
3306 
3307   Args:
3308     x: A Tensor/IndexedSlices/Operation or a list or tuple of them.
3309     p: A Tensor to return for entries in `x` that are Operations.
3310 
3311   Returns:
3312     A list of Tensors or IndexedSlices.
3313   """
3314   if not isinstance(x, (list, _basetuple)):
3315     x = [x]
3316 
3317   l = []
3318   for v in x:
3319     if isinstance(v, ops.Operation):
3320       v = with_dependencies([v], p)
3321     v = ops.convert_to_tensor_or_indexed_slices(v)
3322     if isinstance(v, ops.Tensor):
3323       l.append(array_ops.identity(v))
3324     else:
3325       l.append(
3326           ops.IndexedSlices(
3327               array_ops.identity(v.values), array_ops.identity(v.indices)))
3328   return l

3331 def _CheckResults(a, b):
3332   assert len(a) == len(b), (
3333       "Values returned by a() and b() must have the same length.")
3334   for x, y in zip(a, b):
3335     assert x.dtype == y.dtype, (
3336         "Values returned by a() [%s] and b() [%s] must have "
3337         "the same type: %s, %s." % (x.name, y.name, x.dtype.name, y.dtype.name))

3340 def with_dependencies(dependencies, output_tensor, name=None):
3341   """Produces the content of `output_tensor` only after `dependencies`.
3342 
3343   In some cases, a user may want the output of an operation to be
3344   consumed externally only after some other dependencies have run
3345   first. This function ensures returns `output_tensor`, but only after all
3346   operations in `dependencies` have run. Note that this means that there is
3347   no guarantee that `output_tensor` will be evaluated after any `dependencies`
3348   have run.
3349 
3350   See also `tf.tuple` and `tf.group`.
3351 
3352   Args:
3353     dependencies: Iterable of operations to run before this op finishes.
3354     output_tensor: A `Tensor` or `IndexedSlices` that will be returned.
3355     name: (Optional) A name for this operation.
3356 
3357   Returns:
3358     Same as `output_tensor`.
3359 
3360   Raises:
3361     TypeError: if `output_tensor` is not a `Tensor` or `IndexedSlices`.
3362   """
3363   if context.executing_eagerly():
3364     return output_tensor
3365   with ops.name_scope(name, "control_dependency",
3366                       list(dependencies) + [output_tensor]) as name:
3367     with ops.colocate_with(output_tensor):
3368       with ops.control_dependencies(dependencies):
3369         output_tensor = ops.convert_to_tensor_or_indexed_slices(output_tensor)
3370         if isinstance(output_tensor, ops.Tensor):
3371           return _Identity(output_tensor, name=name)
3372         else:
3373           return ops.IndexedSlices(
3374               _Identity(output_tensor.values, name=name), output_tensor.indices,
3375               output_tensor.dense_shape)
3376 
3377 
3378 def _GroupControlDeps(dev, deps, name=None):
3379   with ops.control_dependencies(deps):
3380     if dev is None:
3381       return no_op(name=name)
3382     else:
3383       with ops.device(dev):
3384         return no_op(name=name)

3387 # TODO(touts): Accept "inputs" as a list.
3388 @tf_export("group")
3389 def group(*inputs, **kwargs):
3390   """Create an op that groups multiple operations.
3391 
3392   When this op finishes, all ops in `inputs` have finished. This op has no
3393   output.
3394 
3395   See also `tf.tuple` and
3396   `tf.control_dependencies`.
3397 
3398   Args:
3399     *inputs: Zero or more tensors to group.
3400     name: A name for this operation (optional).
3401 
3402   Returns:
3403     An Operation that executes all its inputs.
3404 
3405   Raises:
3406     ValueError: If an unknown keyword argument is provided.
3407   """
3408   if context.executing_eagerly():
3409     return None
3410   name = kwargs.pop("name", None)
3411   if kwargs:
3412     raise ValueError("Unknown keyword arguments: " + ", ".join(kwargs.keys()))
3413   with ops.name_scope(name, "group_deps", inputs) as name:
3414     # Grouping no inputs means do nothing
3415     if not inputs:
3416       return no_op(name=name)
3417 
3418     # Sorts *inputs according to their devices.
3419     ops_on_device = {}  # device -> operations specified on the device.
3420     for inp in nest.flatten(inputs):
3421       if not hasattr(inp, "device"):
3422         raise TypeError("Expected tf.group() expected Tensor arguments not "
3423                         "'%s' with type '%s'" % (inp, type(inp)))
3424       dev = inp.device
3425       if dev in ops_on_device:
3426         ops_on_device[dev].append(inp)
3427       else:
3428         ops_on_device[dev] = [inp]
3429     if len(ops_on_device) == 1:
3430       # 1-level tree. The root node is the returned NoOp node.
3431       (dev, deps), = ops_on_device.items()
3432       return _GroupControlDeps(dev, deps, name=name)
3433 
3434     # 2-level tree. The root node is the returned NoOp node.
3435     # deps contains 1 NoOp node for each device.
3436     deps = []
3437 
3438     def device_key(dev):
3439       """A sort key that allows None to be compared to strings."""
3440       return "" if dev is None else dev
3441 
3442     for dev in sorted(six.iterkeys(ops_on_device), key=device_key):
3443       deps.append(_GroupControlDeps(dev, ops_on_device[dev]))
3444 
3445     with ops.control_dependencies(deps):
3446       return no_op(name=name)
3447

3449 @tf_export("tuple")
3450 def tuple(tensors, name=None, control_inputs=None):  # pylint: disable=redefined-builtin
3451   """Group tensors together.
3452 
3453   This creates a tuple of tensors with the same values as the `tensors`
3454   argument, except that the value of each tensor is only returned after the
3455   values of all tensors have been computed.
3456 
3457   `control_inputs` contains additional ops that have to finish before this op
3458   finishes, but whose outputs are not returned.
3459 
3460   This can be used as a "join" mechanism for parallel computations: all the
3461   argument tensors can be computed in parallel, but the values of any tensor
3462   returned by `tuple` are only available after all the parallel computations
3463   are done.
3464 
3465   See also `tf.group` and
3466   `tf.control_dependencies`.
3467 
3468   Args:
3469     tensors: A list of `Tensor`s or `IndexedSlices`, some entries can be `None`.
3470     name: (optional) A name to use as a `name_scope` for the operation.
3471     control_inputs: List of additional ops to finish before returning.
3472 
3473   Returns:
3474     Same as `tensors`.
3475 
3476   Raises:
3477     ValueError: If `tensors` does not contain any `Tensor` or `IndexedSlices`.
3478     TypeError: If `control_inputs` is not a list of `Operation` or `Tensor`
3479       objects.
3480 
3481   """
3482   if context.executing_eagerly():
3483     return tensors
3484   with ops.name_scope(name, "tuple", tensors) as name:
3485     tensors = [t if (isinstance(t, ops.Operation)
3486                      or tensor_util.is_tensor(t)
3487                      or t is None)
3488                else ops.convert_to_tensor(t) for t in tensors]
3489     gating_ops = [t if isinstance(t, ops.Operation) else t.op for t in tensors
3490                   if t is not None]
3491     if control_inputs:
3492       for c in control_inputs:
3493         if isinstance(c, ops.Tensor):
3494           c = c.op
3495         elif not isinstance(c, ops.Operation):
3496           raise TypeError("Control input must be Operation or Tensor: %s" % c)
3497         gating_ops.append(c)
3498     # Note that in order to ensure ordering in the pbtxt, we must take care to
3499     # ensure the order here.
3500     gating_ops = sorted(set(gating_ops), key=lambda op: op._id)  # Uniquify ops.
3501     if not gating_ops:
3502       raise ValueError("Must have at least one Tensor: %s" % tensors)
3503     gate = group(*gating_ops)
3504     tpl = []
3505     for t in tensors:
3506       if tensor_util.is_tensor(t):
3507         tpl.append(with_dependencies([gate], t))
3508       elif isinstance(t, ops.Operation):
3509         with ops.control_dependencies([gate]):
3510           tpl.append(group(t))
3511       else:
3512         tpl.append(None)
3513     return tpl

3516 def _assert_at_most_n_true(predicates, n, msg):
3517   """Returns an Assert op that checks that at most n predicates are True.
3518 
3519   Args:
3520     predicates: list of bool scalar tensors.
3521     n: maximum number of true predicates allowed.
3522     msg: Error message.
3523   """
3524   preds_c = array_ops.stack(predicates, name="preds_c")
3525   num_true_conditions = math_ops.reduce_sum(
3526       math_ops.cast(preds_c, dtypes.int32), name="num_true_conds")
3527   condition = math_ops.less_equal(num_true_conditions,
3528                                   constant_op.constant(n, name="n_true_conds"))
3529   preds_names = ", ".join(getattr(p, "name", "?") for p in predicates)
3530   error_msg = [
3531       "%s: more than %d conditions (%s) evaluated as True:" %
3532       (msg, n, preds_names), preds_c
3533   ]
3534   return Assert(condition, data=error_msg, summarize=len(predicates))

3537 def _case_create_default_action(predicates, actions):
3538   """Creates default action for a list of actions and their predicates.
3539 
3540   It uses the input actions to select an arbitrary as default and makes sure
3541   that corresponding predicates have valid values.
3542 
3543   Args:
3544     predicates: a list of bool scalar tensors
3545     actions: a list of callable objects which return tensors.
3546 
3547   Returns:
3548     a callable
3549   """
3550   k = len(predicates) - 1  # could pick any
3551   predicate, action = predicates[k], actions[k]
3552   other_predicates, other_actions = predicates[:k], actions[:k]
3553 
3554   def default_action():
3555     others_msg = ("Implementation error: "
3556                   "selected default action #%d was called, but some of other "
3557                   "predicates are True: " % k)
3558     default_msg = ("Input error: "
3559                    "None of conditions evaluated as True:",
3560                    array_ops.stack(predicates, name="preds_c"))
3561     with ops.control_dependencies([
3562         _assert_at_most_n_true(other_predicates, n=0, msg=others_msg),
3563         Assert(predicate, data=default_msg)
3564     ]):
3565       return action()
3566 
3567   return default_action, other_predicates, other_actions

3570 def _case_verify_and_canonicalize_args(pred_fn_pairs, exclusive, name,
3571                                        allow_python_preds):
3572   """Verifies input arguments for the case function.
3573 
3574   Args:
3575     pred_fn_pairs: Dict or list of pairs of a boolean scalar tensor,
3576                    and a callable which returns a list of tensors.
3577     exclusive: True iff at most one predicate is allowed to evaluate to `True`.
3578     name: A name for the case operation.
3579     allow_python_preds: if true, pred_fn_pairs may contain Python bools in
3580                         addition to boolean Tensors
3581   Raises:
3582     TypeError: If `pred_fn_pairs` is not a list/dictionary.
3583     TypeError: If `pred_fn_pairs` is a list but does not contain 2-tuples.
3584     TypeError: If `fns[i]` is not callable for any i, or `default` is not
3585                callable.
3586 
3587   Returns:
3588     a tuple <list of scalar bool tensors, list of callables>.
3589   """
3590   if not isinstance(pred_fn_pairs, (list, _basetuple, dict)):
3591     raise TypeError("fns must be a list, tuple, or dict")
3592 
3593   if isinstance(pred_fn_pairs, collections.OrderedDict):
3594     pred_fn_pairs = pred_fn_pairs.items()
3595   elif isinstance(pred_fn_pairs, dict):
3596     pred_fn_pairs = sorted(pred_fn_pairs.items(), key=lambda item: item[0].name)
3597     if not exclusive:
3598       logging.warn("%s: An unordered dictionary of predicate/fn pairs was "
3599                    "provided, but exclusive=False. The order of conditional "
3600                    "tests is deterministic but not guaranteed.", name)
3601   for pred_fn_pair in pred_fn_pairs:
3602     if not isinstance(pred_fn_pair, _basetuple) or len(pred_fn_pair) != 2:
3603       raise TypeError("Each entry in pred_fn_pairs must be a 2-tuple")
3604     pred, fn = pred_fn_pair
3605 
3606     if isinstance(pred, ops.Tensor):
3607       if pred.dtype != dtypes.bool:
3608         raise TypeError("pred must be Tensor of type bool: %s" % pred.name)
3609     elif not allow_python_preds:
3610       raise TypeError("pred must be a Tensor, got: %s" % pred)
3611     elif not isinstance(pred, bool):
3612       raise TypeError("pred must be a Tensor or bool, got: %s" % pred)
3613 
3614     if not callable(fn):
3615       raise TypeError("fn for pred %s must be callable." % pred.name)
3616 
3617   predicates, actions = zip(*pred_fn_pairs)
3618   return predicates, actions
3619 
3620 
3621 def _case_helper(cond_fn, pred_fn_pairs, default,
3622                  exclusive, name, allow_python_preds=False, **cond_kwargs):
3623   """Implementation of case that allows for different cond functions.
3624 
3625   Args:
3626     cond_fn: method that has signature and semantics of `cond` above.
3627     pred_fn_pairs: Dict or list of pairs of a boolean scalar tensor, and a
3628                    callable which returns a list of tensors.
3629     default: Optional callable that returns a list of tensors.
3630     exclusive: True iff at most one predicate is allowed to evaluate to `True`.
3631     name: A name for this operation (optional).
3632     allow_python_preds: if true, pred_fn_pairs may contain Python bools in
3633                         addition to boolean Tensors
3634     **cond_kwargs: keyword arguments that will be passed to `cond_fn`.
3635 
3636   Returns:
3637     The tensors returned by the first pair whose predicate evaluated to True, or
3638     those returned by `default` if none does.
3639 
3640   Raises:
3641     TypeError: If `pred_fn_pairs` is not a list/dictionary.
3642     TypeError: If `pred_fn_pairs` is a list but does not contain 2-tuples.
3643     TypeError: If `fns[i]` is not callable for any i, or `default` is not
3644                callable.
3645   """
3646   predicates, actions = _case_verify_and_canonicalize_args(
3647       pred_fn_pairs, exclusive, name, allow_python_preds)
3648   with ops.name_scope(name, "case", [predicates]):
3649     if default is None:
3650       default, predicates, actions = _case_create_default_action(
3651           predicates, actions)
3652     fn = default
3653     # To eval conditions in direct order we create nested conditions in reverse:
3654     #   cond_fn(c[0], true_fn=.., false_fn=cond_fn(c[1], ...))
3655     for predicate, action in reversed(list(zip(predicates, actions))):
3656       fn = functools.partial(
3657           cond_fn, predicate, true_fn=action, false_fn=fn, **cond_kwargs)
3658     if exclusive:
3659       with ops.control_dependencies([
3660           _assert_at_most_n_true(
3661               predicates, n=1, msg="Input error: exclusive=True")
3662       ]):
3663         return fn()
3664     else:
3665       return fn()
3666

3668 @tf_export("case")
3669 def case(pred_fn_pairs,
3670          default=None,
3671          exclusive=False,
3672          strict=False,
3673          name="case"):
3674   """Create a case operation.
3675 
3676   The `pred_fn_pairs` parameter is a dict or list of pairs of size N.
3677   Each pair contains a boolean scalar tensor and a python callable that
3678   creates the tensors to be returned if the boolean evaluates to True.
3679   `default` is a callable generating a list of tensors. All the callables
3680   in `pred_fn_pairs` as well as `default` (if provided) should return the same
3681   number and types of tensors.
3682 
3683   If `exclusive==True`, all predicates are evaluated, and an exception is
3684   thrown if more than one of the predicates evaluates to `True`.
3685   If `exclusive==False`, execution stops at the first predicate which
3686   evaluates to True, and the tensors generated by the corresponding function
3687   are returned immediately. If none of the predicates evaluate to True, this
3688   operation returns the tensors generated by `default`.
3689 
3690   `tf.case` supports nested structures as implemented in
3691   `tensorflow.python.util.nest`. All of the callables must return the same
3692   (possibly nested) value structure of lists, tuples, and/or named tuples.
3693   Singleton lists and tuples form the only exceptions to this: when returned by
3694   a callable, they are implicitly unpacked to single values. This
3695   behavior is disabled by passing `strict=True`.
3696 
3697   If an unordered dictionary is used for `pred_fn_pairs`, the order of the
3698   conditional tests is not guaranteed. However, the order is guaranteed to be
3699   deterministic, so that variables created in conditional branches are created
3700   in fixed order across runs.
3701 
3702   **Example 1:**
3703 
3704   Pseudocode:
3705 
3706   ```
3707   if (x < y) return 17;
3708   else return 23;
3709   ```
3710 
3711   Expressions:
3712 
3713   ```python
3714   f1 = lambda: tf.constant(17)
3715   f2 = lambda: tf.constant(23)
3716   r = case([(tf.less(x, y), f1)], default=f2)
3717   ```
3718 
3719   **Example 2:**
3720 
3721   Pseudocode:
3722 
3723   ```
3724   if (x < y && x > z) raise OpError("Only one predicate may evaluate true");
3725   if (x < y) return 17;
3726   else if (x > z) return 23;
3727   else return -1;
3728   ```
3729 
3730   Expressions:
3731 
3732   ```python
3733   def f1(): return tf.constant(17)
3734   def f2(): return tf.constant(23)
3735   def f3(): return tf.constant(-1)
3736   r = case({tf.less(x, y): f1, tf.greater(x, z): f2},
3737            default=f3, exclusive=True)
3738   ```
3739 
3740   Args:
3741     pred_fn_pairs: Dict or list of pairs of a boolean scalar tensor and a
3742                    callable which returns a list of tensors.
3743     default: Optional callable that returns a list of tensors.
3744     exclusive: True iff at most one predicate is allowed to evaluate to `True`.
3745     strict: A boolean that enables/disables 'strict' mode; see above.
3746     name: A name for this operation (optional).
3747 
3748   Returns:
3749     The tensors returned by the first pair whose predicate evaluated to True, or
3750     those returned by `default` if none does.
3751 
3752   Raises:
3753     TypeError: If `pred_fn_pairs` is not a list/dictionary.
3754     TypeError: If `pred_fn_pairs` is a list but does not contain 2-tuples.
3755     TypeError: If `fns[i]` is not callable for any i, or `default` is not
3756                callable.
3757   """
3758   return _case_helper(cond, pred_fn_pairs, default, exclusive, name,
3759                       allow_python_preds=False, strict=strict)

3779 def from_control_flow_context_def(context_def, import_scope=None):
3780   """Deserializes `context_def` into the appropriate ControlFlowContext.
3781 
3782   Args:
3783     context_def: ControlFlowContextDef proto
3784     import_scope: Optional `string`. Name scope to add.
3785 
3786   Returns:
3787     A ControlFlowContext subclass
3788   """
3789   if context_def.HasField("cond_ctxt"):
3790     return CondContext.from_proto(context_def.cond_ctxt,
3791                                   import_scope=import_scope)
3792   if context_def.HasField("while_ctxt"):
3793     return WhileContext.from_proto(context_def.while_ctxt,
3794                                    import_scope=import_scope)
3795   raise NotImplementedError("Unknown ControlFlowContextDef field: %s"
3796                             % context_def.WhichOneof("ctxt"))
